title: old fashioned lemon pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in egg yolks.
Add water mixed with corn meal.
Add lemon juice and grated rind of lemons. Lastly, fold in beaten egg whites.
Cook on unbaked pie crust. This makes 2 large pies. Start at 350°, then turn to 300° after starts to brown (about 10 minutes).
Cook about 25 minutes all together.
I cook these pies on a preheated cookie sheet to help the crust get done on the bottom.

title: chip's cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease square pan (8 or 9-inch).
Mix ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: Cut chicken into smaller pieces and place chicken in the beaten eggs for about 1 hour.
Coat the chicken in bread crumbs and brown in oleo on all sides.
Place in casserole pan.
Sprinkle cheese over the chicken, then add the mushrooms, then pour chicken broth. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Remove cover the last 10 minutes.

title: beef and gravy
directions: Cook meat until almost done.
Add potatoes and onions and cook until done.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix flour in 1/2 cup water. Add to beef and cook about 3 minutes.

title: rhubarb and raisin pie
directions: Prepare crusts.
Mix remaining ingredients together except for margarine.
Pour into crust; dot top with margarine.
Add top vented crust.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 350° until crust is browned.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put through a cookie press.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix and set aside molasses, boiling water and soda.
Mix until crumbly the flour, oil, salt and sugar.
Save 1 cup of crumbs for top of cake.
Add the liquid to the remaining crumbs and
pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread reserved crumbs evenly over top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: If fresh squash is used, parboil until almost tender and drain.
Dot casserole dish with 1/2 stick butter.
Place 1/2 bag stuffing on bottom of dish.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over stuffing.
Top with the rest of the stuffing and dot with butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix cornmeal, eggs, corn, peppers, oil, buttermilk, onions and cheese.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 30-35 minutes our until brown on top.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound each breast until they are as thin as possible.
Place a thin slice of ham and a slice of cheese on each half of breast. Be sure cheese does not come near the edge.
Fold over the other side of breast.
Pin edges together with round toothpick (pin through skin if possible).
Dip breasts in beaten egg; sprinkle with Gold 'N Crust.

title: five-cup salad
directions: Mix all together; chill thoroughly.
Great served with chicken.

title: lemon cake custard
directions: Into a small bowl of mixer, put 3 egg whites and salt.
Beat on number 8 speed until stiff but still moist.
Into large bowl of mixer, put 3 egg yolks, sugar, butter and flour.
Beat on number 3 speed until blended.
Add milk slowly to yolk mixture still beating on number 3 speed.
Add lemon rind, juice and egg whites. Beat on number 1 speed only until blended.
Pour into buttered custard cups.
Set in pan of hot water.
Bake in 325° oven about 50 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Put pie crust in 9-inch pan as directed. In large bowl, combine ingredients. Pour into pan. Bake 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350°. Bake 40 or 50 minutes more, until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Store in refrigerator. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: stir-fried vegetables(microwave)
directions: Preheat a 10-inch browning skillet on Full power for 5 minutes.
Quickly add oil, then all vegetables.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes on Full power, covered with lid.
Stir after 3 minutes. Quickly add cornstarch and bouillon, dissolved in 1/2 cup water. Add remaining seasonings.
Cook another 3 minutes on Full power, uncovered, stirring after 1 1/2 minutes.

title: old-fashioned chicken pie
directions: Line bottom of baking dish with chicken.
Spoon mixture of soup and water over chicken.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Top with mixture of buttermilk, flour and margarine.
Pour broth over layers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: enchiladas con pollo
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine 1/2 of cheese with next 7 ingredients and mix with 1 cup of taco sauce.
Microwave until soft; add 1/3 cup filling.
Roll up and place seam side down in a buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread remaining sauce over tortillas; cover with foil and bake 30 minutes.
Remove foil and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake until cheese melts (approximately 3 minutes).
Serve immediately.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need 1 (8-inch) plastic kid's bucket (new) and silk flower bunch.

title: blueberry dream pie
directions: Mix sugar and cream cheese well. Prepare Dream Whip as directed on box. Add Dream Whip and vanilla to sugar and cheese. Add nuts and mix well. Pour mixture into baked pie shells. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Before serving, add blueberries to top. Makes 2 pies.

title: chopped bread
directions: Flatten dough out; add ingredients to dough.
Take four corners and pinch together in middle.
Chop dough and ingredients into pieces and combine well.
Shape into ball.
Place on lined baking sheet.
Let dough sit at room temperature until it doubles in volume.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into pieces and serve hot.

title: chocolate town cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch cake pans. Cream sugar and shortening in mixing bowl.
Add eggs one at a time; add vanilla.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with milk.
Make heavy paste of cocoa and boiling water; add and blend well.
Bake about 35 minutes until done (milk may be soured by adding 1 teaspoon vinegar to milk).

title: chili con carne
directions: Start to cook all together, then turn to low and simmer.

title: layered club salad
directions: In large bowl, layer ingredients.
Spread mayonnaise on top. Yields 8 servings.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add all other ingredients and stir until pecans are well coated.
Pour into buttered baking sheet. Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Yields 1 1/2 quarts.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Bake foil wrapped chicken breasts 2 hours.
Salt, pepper and debone chicken. Reserve juices.
Grease a 3-quart casserole.
Mix soup, juices from chicken and seasonings.
Layer tortillas, large chicken pieces, onion, cheese and soup mix. Make several layers. Top with cheese. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: frozen pineapple and fruit salad
directions: Work in well 2 tablespoons mayonnaise with 1 package cream cheese, adding a pinch of salt.
Whip 1/2 pint heavy cream and add 1/4 pound soft marshmallows.
Cut in small pieces.
Combine and add pineapple, cut in small pieces and fruit cocktail; all well drained.
Add the maraschino cherries.
Put in ice cube tray and freeze until firm, overnight if possible.

title: mom's special punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Can be used to leave small rolled ball treats for Santa.
Can be eaten in bowl with milk and honey.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks; beat well, then add flour, soda and sour cream.
Fold in egg whites (beaten stiff). Bake for 1 hour at 350° in 2 loaf pans.
Good.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Note:
Have the popcorn in a brown bag.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar and cream cheese.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Add nuts. Divide equally and fill pie crusts, forming a well from center out to about 1 1/2 inches from edge.
Pour one can of pie filling into each pie, filling the well.
Cover and store in refrigerator. Serve chilled.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Mix first six ingredients together well.
Add chicken. Separate crescent rolls into 8 rectangles and seal perforations. Spoon approximately 1/4 cup chicken mixture onto one side of each rectangle over mixture and seal the three open sides.
Brush tops with 1 tablespoon melted margarine; sprinkle with the seasoned bread crumbs (optional).
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Gradually beat in sugar, salt and vanilla.
Fold in nuts.
Place on buttered, floured cookie sheet by spoonfuls.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes at 325°.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender, cool, peel and grate or chop finely or rice.
Heat butter/margarine (1/4 cup) with soup. Blend sour cream, onion and cheese into soup.
Stir in potatoes. Place in buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole (you may choose to spray casserole dish with Pam).
Mix corn flakes with melted butter/margarine and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix the three meats together.
Add the corn flakes, milk and eggs.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Baste with a mixture of remaining ingredients at least 3 times while baking.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: potato soup
directions: Place potatoes in large saucepan with 4 cups water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until tender; drain.
Add milk and vegetables to drained potatoes; bring to a gentle boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat.
Add cheese, butter and season to taste.
Heat over low heat, stirring frequently, until cheese is melted and vegetables are tender-crisp.
Makes 6 one cup servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Using mixer, cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and flavoring to creamed butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, to your creamed ingredients, mixing continuously.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Add apple juice concentrate to apples in a saucepan until partially cooked.
Mix cornstarch and spices with a little of the juice (take a tablespoon of the juice out of the pan), then add mixture to the apples.
Pour apple mixture into pie shell.
Dot with butter and apply top crust.
Cover outer edges of crust with aluminum foil for 20 minutes, then remove.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until crust is brown and apples are soft.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in smaller bowl.
Mix all wet ingredients in large bowl, then add dry ingredients to wet.
Fold in pecans and raisins last, if desired.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed dates
directions: Cream margarine, blend in syrup, peel, vanilla and salt.
Add sugar and mix with spoon, then knead with hands.
Wrap in foil and chill 24 hours.
Wrap each nut with 1/2 teaspoon candy and stuff into dates.

title: one egg cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar until light. Add the egg, beating vigorously. Add the vanilla extract. Add the flour alternately with the milk. Mix until batter is smooth. Pour into greased cake pans. Bake in oven (375°) 25 minutes. Makes two 8-inch layers.

title: chicken and pasta
directions: Coat nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add chicken, pepper cubes, mushrooms and minced garlic.
Saute 4 minutes or until chicken is lightly browned.
Add chicken broth.
Reduce heat to medium and simmer, uncovered, 2 minutes.
Remove chicken mixture from heat and set aside.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in greased casserole dish. Mix egg and milk; pour over bread slices and sprinkle with cheese. Cook sausage; drain off fat and sprinkle over bread and egg mixture. Sprinkle with more cheese; cover with foil, place in refrigerator over night. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: broccoli puff(serves 6)
directions: Cook frozen broccoli according to package directions, omitting salt called for.
Drain thoroughly.
Place broccoli cuts in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Stir together condensed soup and cheese; gradually add milk, mayonnaise and beaten egg to soup mixture, stirring until well blended.
Pour over broccoli in baking dish.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle evenly over soup mix and broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until lightly browned.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Place pickling spices in boiling water.
Add cabbage leaves. Cook leaves until bright green, 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove; set aside.
Brown hamburger meat; drain fat.
Add salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, A.1. steak sauce, red wine vinegar, horseradish, pressed garlic and minced onion, then mix ingredients.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until soft.
Remove from oven.
Cut in half and remove potatoes from shell.
In mixing bowl, mix while still hot the butter, milk, salt and pepper until smooth.
Spoon the mixture back into the shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes. (Potatoes can be topped with Cheddar cheese and/or almond slices, if desired.)
Can be prepared in advance.

title: warm lemon pudding
directions: In 1-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt, if desired.
Stir in 1/4 cup of the milk, mixing until cornstarch dissolves.
Add remaining milk.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 3 minutes, whisking mixture well after 2 minutes.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Add onions and celery. Saute until vegetables are soft.
Add okra, tomatoes and bay leaf. Simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: sauteed shrimp and rice
directions: Boil, peel and devein shrimp. (If large, may cut up in pieces.)
Set aside.

title: french bread surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix beef, ketchup, mustard, salt and soup.
Slice bread the long way and scoop out the middle.
Fill in space with mixture.
Take 8 slices of any kind of cheese; break in half and lay over mixture.
Close bread by wrapping in tinfoil and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: yellow squash pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except coconut, using hand mixer or blender.
Last add coconut and pour in pie shell.
Cook 30 minutes in 425° oven and then reduce heat to 375° for last 30 minutes until done.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all together.
Place in casserole with sprinkles of paprika and a few bread crumbs.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix thoroughly and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Mix all together and pour into 3 unbaked pie shells.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 pies.

title: jerry's ice cream dough(kolacky)
directions: Gradually add flour to ice cream and butter.
Make into rolls. Put in wax paper, freeze and then cut into circular slices.
Put them on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Dent and lightly flour each slice.
Fill with preferred prepared fillings.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until rosy.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Makes over 6 dozen kolacky.

title: veggie quiche
directions: Melt butter in a large frying pan.
Add onion, green pepper, zucchini and mushrooms.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring at times.
Add tomato and flour.
Stir to blend flour.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle half of cheese in pie shell.
Add veggies.
Pour milk mixture evenly over veggies. Sprinkle with rest of cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes approximately 6 servings.
(Recipe also works well using a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and low-fat cheese.)

title: ice cream sandwich
directions: Joshua gets his Grandmama to go to the ice box; points to ice box freezer.
Grandmama opens freezer and takes out ice cream sandwich.
Joshua sits down on the couch, unwraps -- then eats. Repeat as Grandmama tolerates!!!

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Good warm or cool.

title: my mother's fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir soda into sour milk.
Sift together all spices and flour; dredge all fruits and nuts in flour mixture.
Be sure all fruits are well coated with flour.
Pour butter, sugar and egg mixture over fruit. Add molasses and milk to fruit.
Stir until all fruits and flour are moistened well.
This may be mixed with the hands.
Bake at 275° for 2 or more hours.
Test with a straw or toothpick for doneness of batter.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, salt and soda.
In a saucepan bring to a boil the margarine, oil, cocoa and water.
Pour the cocoa mixture over the flour mixture.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour batter into a greased jelly roll pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Pour frosting over cake while it is in the pan and as soon as it is removed from the oven.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients and pat on bottom of pan.
Mix next four ingredients and pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 325° in a 13 x 9-inch Pam sprayed cake pan for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: best beef goulash
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef with chopped onion and chopped green pepper.
Mix soups, mushrooms with liquid, water, salt and pepper and add to meat, onions and peppers.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Mix meat mixture with cooked macaroni and place into greased casserole.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 325°.

title: peaches and cream homemade ice cream
directions: Blend together in blender, canned milk, sugar, 1 cup whole milk and peaches.
Pour into freezing churn.
Mix together in blender 1 cup whole milk, vanilla pudding, cornstarch and vanilla flavoring and pour into churn. Finish filling churn with whole milk.

title: pineapple mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water and let cool. Add remaining ingredients.
Put in mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken and cut into pieces.
Mix soup, sour cream, onion, chilies and chicken.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into slightly greased baking dish.
Roll cheese in flour shells and place on top of chicken mixture.
Top with rest of chicken mixture, cheese and chopped green onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until good and hot.

title: caviar pie
directions: Mash hard-cooked eggs.
Mix with butter and half of chopped onion.
Spread evenly on the bottom of a 9-inch pie plate. Refrigerate for at least 1/2 hour.
Blend mayonnaise with chopped parsley.
Spread over egg mixture.
Spread sour cream over parsley and mayonnaise layer.
Combine caviar, chopped onion and lemon juice.
Gently drain caviar mixture and spread over sour cream just before serving.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Mix stuffing, margarine and water; set aside.
Combine mayonnaise, milk, eggs, onions, celery and salt and mix well with stuffing mixture.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish 1/2 of the stuffing.
Layer in chicken and top with other half of stuffing.
Spread with soup and bake, uncovered, at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: toffee squares
directions: Cream butter, add brown sugar and mix until light and fluffy. Add beaten egg yolk, vanilla and sifted flour.
Spread thinly on jelly roll-size pan.
Bake at 350° about 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown.
Melt chocolate in top of double boiler, spread on cookie surface while still warm.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Cut in squares while warm and let cool.

title: pull apart cinnamon rolls
directions: Let bread dough thaw and then knead well.
Melt butter or margarine and set aside.
Pull dough apart about the size of a walnut.
Roll in butter or margarine and then sugar mixture.
Drop into a Bundt pan in layers.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven; cool 5 minutes, then invert onto plate.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Add the remainder of ingredients. Needs to marinate 24 hours before serving.
Will keep several days in fridge.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Bottom Layer:
Cream together sugar, oleo and pretzels.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: red fruity punch
directions: Chill 7-Up, Hawaiian Punch and pineapple just prior to preparing punch.
Mix 7-Up/lemon-lime drink, Hawaiian Punch and pineapple juice together in a large punch bowl.
Add frozen strawberries and stir to break up.
Garnish with orange slices when serving.

title: spicy guacamole
directions: Mash pulp from avocados well.
Add thick 'n chunky salsa and tomatoes; stir well.
Add lemon juice and salt to taste.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cheese dip
directions: Soften cheese.	Blend
in blender with beer, garlic and salt. Scoop out middle of
bread;
use
this to dip in cheese mixture which
you	pour into bread.
Tear up extra loaf into small pieces for dipping purpose.

title: pecan delights
directions: In a large saucepan, combine first four ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until sugar is dissolved. Gradually add milk and mix well.
Cook until firm ball stage (248°). Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Fold in pecans. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Chill until firm.

title: tuna casserole(stove top casserole)
directions: Cook macaroni.
Fry onion in butter.
Add onion, soup, mixed vegetables, tuna and milk to macaroni.
Simmer about 15 minutes. Season to taste.

title: coffee frappe
directions: Prepare instant coffee and let chill. Add the sugar to the coffee. Let ice cream begin to soften.

title: baked spaghetti dinner(makes 6 servings)
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
In skillet, brown beef in butter, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; add 1/4 cup flour, nonfat dry milk, salt, pepper and half of soup mix.
Blend water in gradually.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Combine remaining soup mix with 1 tablespoon flour, then blend with sour cream.
Fold into cooked spaghetti; place into 2-quart buttered casserole, pushing up on sides to form a well in center.
Pour meat mixture in center.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake for 25 minutes in 350° oven or until bread crumbs are brown.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Put half the bread mix in the bottom. Spread meat, onion and 1 green pepper over the bread mix. Sprinkle 1 cup shredded cheese over the mixture. Spread remaining mix on top of the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: sparkling punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except ginger ale; chill several hours.
At serving time, slowly pour in ginger ale.
Serve over cracked ice.
If desired, garnish with frosted Tokay grapes. Makes about 10 to 12 servings.

title: nanaimo bars
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add sugar, cocoa, vanilla and egg.
Cook over medium heat stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Stir in coconut, graham cracker crumbs and nuts.
Pat mixture into a buttered 8 x 8 or 9 x 9 baking pan.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Beat ingredients well, except bacon drippings .
Heat (preferably) in a cast-iron frying pan to medium-high.
Add bacon drippings to pan.
Pour a small amount of batter in pan for heat and consistency test.
Hold handle and tilt pan so batter spreads to circular shape.
Turn over when lightly browned.

title: fran's lemon bars
directions: Mix crust ingredients well and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased).
Bake in unheated oven at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In mixing bowl, place egg, broccoli, corn, onion, salt and pepper.
In saucepan, melt butter and add stuffing mix; toss to coat.
Stir in half stuffing.
Mix into vegetables.
Put in 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: coconut crispies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread coconut on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes until golden.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.

title: funi salad
directions: Brown nuts and seed in butter.
Mix together cabbage and onions.
Just before serving, mix all together with dressing.

title: garlic sauce
directions: Brown the butter and add lemon juice and garlic.
Season to taste.

title: tomato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Good with fish and cookouts.

title: french apple crumb cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix and sift dry ingredients into a mixing bowl.
Cut in the shortening until crumbly.
Add the egg, mixing well.
Press half of the mixture into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Spread with the applesauce and lightly press the remaining dough mixture over the sauce.
Sprinkle with the brown sugar.
Bake 45 minutes, then turn off oven; open oven door a little and let cake sit another 30 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired. Favorite spices may be added to the applesauce as well.
Serves 8.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Press 1 can into each of 2 cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes; cool.
Mix cream cheese, dressing and Ranch dressing. Spread on rolls.
Sprinkle vegetables (olives, carrots, broccoli, cauliflower).
Chill for 4 hours.
Cut with pizza cutter into bars.

title: russell stover candy
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add the cream, butter and sugar.
Add the rest of ingredients. Chill. Roll into balls. Chill overnight. Roll in white or dark chocolate, melted. Drop on wax paper.

title: noodles in butter
directions: Drop the noodles in boiling, salted water for 10 minutes; do not cook them too soft, they must still be firm when bitten. Drain immediately.
Put a pan over low heat and add the butter. As it melts, tip in the noodles and season with salt and freshly ground black pepper.
Turn the noodles over and over until they are hot and coated with melted butter.
Pour into a heated dish and serve immediately.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together.
Grease pan and pour in mix.
Pour 1/2 cup melted oleo on top of mix, then sprinkle 2 cups of crushed corn flakes on top and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: lumpia
directions: Fry ground beef until brown and drain.
Finely chop the vegetables.
Mix together ground beef, vegetables, egg yolk, allspice, salt, pepper, soy sauce and stir-fry sauce.
Put about a heaped tablespoonful of mixture into each lumpia skin.
Wrap according to directions and seal with egg white.
Fry in oil on each side until golden brown.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°.
Lower temperature to 350° and bake about 35 minutes or until custard is firm.

title: linguine salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve at room temperature.

title: "crepes"
directions: In bowl, combine flour, eggs, 1/2 milk, melted butter, salt and sugar; mix well with a whisk.
The batter should be very thick.
Work it until it is very smooth, then add the other 1/2 cup milk, cold water and oil.
Stir well.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add buttermilk all at once.
Stir with a fork until dough makes a ball.
Turn out; knead 1/2 minute.
Roll out 3/8-inch thick.
Cut out.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 450° for 12 minutes.
Makes 12 to 15 biscuits.

title: egg rolls
directions: Note:
Need 1 package of egg roll wrappers.

title: pasta and bean soup
directions: In large saucepan combine broth, tomato juice, macaroni, garlic, and carrots; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium; simmer for 4 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt ingredients together.
(You can do this in the microwave 30 seconds at a time, then stir).
Pour onto 1 box Crispix cereal. Stir until well coated.
Take a big container with lid and layer the cereal mixture with 10x sugar and shake!.

title: green pie
directions: Mix the Eagle Brand milk, limeade and Cool Whip together. Then add just enough green food coloring to make it green. Pour into the pie crusts. Chill until ready to serve.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Put ingredients in pot in order listed.
Cover and cook on high 2 to 3 hours, or on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Stir occasionally. Serves 4 to 6.

title: igloo
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Place cake on ovenproof platter.
In large mixing bowl, beat together egg whites, salt and cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff.
Spread ice cream over cake.
Top with peaches.
Spread meringue over cake top and sides, covering entire surface.
Place cake with dish on baking sheet.
Bake for 3 to 5 minutes, until meringue browns slightly. Serve immediately.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine cream cheese and margarine, beating until smooth.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Yields enough for 3 layer cake.

title: fried chicken
directions: Drain chicken; salt and pepper chicken pieces.
Sift flour in a bowl, pour milk in another bowl, add seasoned salt and garlic powder to milk.
Dip pieces of chicken in milk mixture and coat in flour.
In deep fryer or heavy skillet, heat oil to 300° and fry chicken until golden brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix altogether and add green grapes and blueberries.

title: west homestead roast beef
directions: Cut beef in 4 to 6 pieces.
Remove most of the fat from the beef.
Wash well in cold water.
Pepper lightly.
Place roasts in large roasting pans.
Add 1/2 onion to each.
Fill pan half full with water.
Bake at 350° for about 5 hours, covered.

title: 4-day coconut cake
directions: On Day 1, mix first 4 ingredients together in large bowl and place in refrigerator.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together and place 4 to 5 slices of bacon on top. Bake at 450° until bacon is done.

title: ms. katherine's oven barbecued chicken
directions: Halve or quarter chickens and dry well.
Place in shallow pan. Mix together the salad oil, minced garlic and paprika.
Pour over chicken and marinate for 3 or 4 hours, turning the chickens every half hour.
Remove from pan and season with salt and pepper.
Place chickens in broiler pan with inside upwards and place broiler about 8-inches from broiler unit.
Baste frequently with the basting sauce.
Place oven control at 350° and cook until tender.
Turn chickens the last 15 minutes of cooking with skin side upwards for skin to brown.

title: rover's rewards - dog biscuits
directions: In large bowl, pour hot water over margarine.
Stir in powdered milk, salt and beaten egg.
Add flour, 1/2 cup at a time, mixing well.
Knead 3 to 4 minutes.
Add more flour to make stiff dough.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness and cut with biscuit cutter. Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 50 minutes. Cool and allow to dry out until hard.
Makes approximately 1 1/4 pounds.

title: orange nuggets
directions: Mix vanilla crumbs, coconut and orange juice concentrate together.
Shape into one-inch balls and place in a flat pan. Chill 3 hours.
Roll in powdered sugar before serving.

title: no-bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Put oats and vanilla in medium sized bowl.
Melt margarine in saucepan, then add all other ingredients.
Boil for 4 to 5 minutes.
(If rainy or wet weather, boil 5 to 6 minutes.)
Pour boiled mixture over oats and mix together.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool.
Makes about 2 dozen. Kids may need some help with the cooking.

title: whole grain batter bread
directions: Combine boiling water, butter, sugar and salt in a large bowl, stirring until butter melts; cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in warm water. Stir dissolved yeast, oats, 2 cups flour and eggs into lukewarm water mixture; mix well. Stir in enough remaining flour to make stiff batter. Place in greased large bowl.

title: norwegian gumdrop cookies
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Mix only until blended, dough will be stiff. Add gumdrops and nuts.
Pour into a well-greased shallow pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into small squares while still warm and dust each piece with powdered sugar.
Store in a closed cookie jar or other closed container.

title: festive crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and chill.
Serve with assorted fresh vegetables.
Yield: 2 cups.
Contains 35 calories (10% from fat) per tablespoon of dip and 1/2 cup vegetables.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased oven dish.

title: steamed carrot pudding
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Grease mold and fill 2/3 full.
Cover with waxed paper.
Steam 1 1/2 hours in boiling water.

title: shrimply delicious(low-fat)
directions: Cook chicken broth, tomatoes, garlic, oregano, basil and salt and pepper in frying pan for about 5 minutes. Stir once in awhile. Add oil. Cook until tomatoes are soft. Add shrimp and wine. Cook until pink; do not overcook.
Serve over white rice.

title: fish bake
directions: Cook haddock and scallops.
Heat 1/3 cup milk and add the shrimp soup.
Pour over fish and bake 350° oven as casserole.

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; debone and tear into bite size pieces.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Put in large casserole dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
tags: cream of chicken soup or celery soup

title: peanut butter-chocolate chip brownies
directions: Set margarine out an hour or two before you're ready to make brownies.
Use one pat of the margarine to grease pan.
Mix margarine and peanut butter together.
Then add sugars; mix.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing.

title: starburst ice cream
directions: Freeze Starburst candies.
When frozen, put in blender and chop into chunky bits.
Thaw out 1/2 gallon sherbet (not all the way).
Blend and mix Starburst chunks and ice cream.
Re-freeze, scoop and serve.

title: hot sauce
directions: Blend together in food processor and refrigerate.

title: edible play dough
directions: Mix until well blended.
For chocolate flavor, add some cocoa while mixing.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Cook all together. Place in baked crust
and cover with meringue made from 2 egg whites.
Brown in oven.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease casserole pan. Tear up bread into pieces and put in bottom of pan. Add both cheeses on top of bread. Beat eggs. Add to the eggs the salt, onion, mustard, cream and sausage and pour over top of cheese. Refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: aloha fruit dip
directions: Stir together non-fruit items.
For beginners, a good way to crush the cookies is to place them in a Ziploc bag, squeeze out air, and roll over bag with a rolling pin until crushed.
Chill several hours to soften macaroons.
Do not stir again or macaroon pieces will become crumbs.
Serve in a bowl surrounded by fruit and enjoy!

title: sweet potato custard
directions: Cook potatoes in oven until done; mash and add ingredients left.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Crumble cheese by hand. Add eggs, onion, parsley and seasonings. Put in enough mayonnaise so it sticks together.
Put in a round bottom bowl and refrigerate.
Turn over onto plate when ready to serve and sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with crackers.

title: diabetic barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer 20 minutes.
May be cooked on any meat without simmering.
Each tablespoon has 10 calories.

title: broccoli peanut picnic slaw
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients to make dressing.
Mix slaw dressing and sugar.
Pour over veggies and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: ho-hum potatoes
directions: Cut scrubbed, unpeeled potatoes into chunks.
Mix the garlic, parsley, melted margarine, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over potatoes; cover and bake at 400° about 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter chocolate cookies(no bakes)
directions: Bring first four ingredients to a boil; remove from heat and add oatmeal and peanut butter.
Stir until mixed well and peanut butter has melted.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.
Cool.

title: creamed meat balls
directions: Mix 1/4 cup of soup and water mixture with the rest of the ingredients.
Make 16 meat balls.
Roll in flour.
Brown in shortening in skillet.
Place meat balls in casserole and put into a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Pour off fat.
Pour remaining soup mixture over meat balls and return to oven for 1/2 hour longer. Stir often.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: chicken-cheese roll-ups
directions: In shallow pan, melt butter in 350° oven.
While butter is melting, mix lemon juice, mustard and dill.
When butter is melted, remove pan from oven.

title: deer salami
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate for 3 days.
Mix well daily. On the 4th day, make into loaves.
Place on rack and bake 8 or 9 hours at 150°.
Do not use higher temperature.

title: carrot log
directions: Stir together carrots, cream cheese, Parmesan cheese and fines herbes in a small mixing bowl.
Cover and chill for at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: susie's pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter.
Add beaten eggs and pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 30 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time and beat well after each egg until light and fluffy.
Crush wafers very fine and add alternately with the milk.
Fold in coconut and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 275° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or little longer.
Moist and delicious.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the first five ingredients.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt, then stir in mixture.
Chill dough; roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Roll in sugar; place 3 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork, crisscrossed.
Bake until set (not hard) in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove to waxed paper to cool.

title: stuffed artichokes with roasted pecans
directions: Drain and reserve artichoke juice. Put rinsed artichokes onto paper towels and cover. Mix the rest of the ingredients until it reaches desired consistency (not soaked, still a little dry/crumbly), adding juice or bread crumbs as necessary. Put pecans on baking sheet and bake in 375° preheated oven for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: poke-a-nut cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions.
Cook in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
After baking, punch holes in cake with a fork.
Frost while hot.
Drain pineapple, but not completely dry.
Spread over frosting; sprinkle with coconut.

title: florence's dill slices
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Dry pickles.
Lay approximately 3 slices of beef on cutting board.
Spread cream cheese mixture on beef overlapping edges.
Roll pickle up in beef and cream cheese mixture.
Chill.
Slice before serving.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, peanut butter and milk together and add Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Pour into pie crusts.
Top with pecans and Butterfinger mixture.
Divide between 2 pies.
Freeze overnight.
Keep frozen until served.

title: italian casserole
directions: In frypan, brown ground beef and onion and drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Pour hot meat mixture into ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: vanilla fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cream, milk, syrup and salt.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Boil slowly, stirring occasionally, to 234° or the soft ball stage.
Remove from heat. Cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat until thick.
Pour into a butter dish to cool before cutting into squares.
Makes 1 1/8 pounds.

title: apricot chicken divine
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Shake chicken in a plastic bag filled with flour and salt until chicken is coated.
Place chicken in a single layer in a shallow baking pan; bake for 25 minutes. Combine apricot preserves, mustard and yogurt.
Spread apricot mixture on chicken; bake for 10 to 15 minutes more, or until done. Just before serving, brown almonds lightly in toaster oven. Sprinkle almonds over chicken and serve over rice.

title: coconut-sour cream dream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions and bake in two 8-inch cake pans.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans and let cool completely.
Split layers in half horizontally to make 4 layers.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut, mixing well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Reserve 1 cup sour cream mixture. Set aside.
Spread remaining mixture between cake layers.
Fold whipped cream into reserved 1 cup sour cream.
Spread on top and sides of cake.
Cover and chill overnight.
Garnish with cherries, if desired.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour and add remaining ingredients.
Cook in slow oven (350° to 375°).

title: salad made in heaven
directions: Drain fruits well and set aside.
Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Add drained fruits and chill until served.

title: scones
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In
a cup, beat together egg and milk with a fork.
Reserve 1 teaspoon for glaze.

title: syllabub
directions: Have all ingredients cold.
Place all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat with egg beater until frothy.
Serve immediately. Yields about 20 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in a small amount of oil until half cooked.
Melt margarine and mix with stuffing mix.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Add zucchini and onion.
Layer casserole with 1/2 of stuffing mix.
Place other ingredients on top.
Top with other 1/2 of stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: slop
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and put in a baking pan.
Bake until Tater Tots are brown and cheese is melted.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan or approximately 28 cupcakes.
Put 1 tablespoon baking soda in 2 1/2 cups boiling water. In a large bowl, put flour, salt, brown sugar and oil. Crumb.
Set aside 1 cup for top.
Mix everything together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in very warm water.
Combine sugar, shortening, salt and scalded milk.
Cool to lukewarm by adding cold water. Blend in yeast mixture, egg and flour.
Mix well.
Grease top of dough and sides of bowl.
Cover.
Rise for 1 hour until double. Stir down.
Spoon into well-greased muffin pans, 1/2 full.
Cover. Let rise 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 18.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into pie shells; cover crust with foil to prevent burning of crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and continue baking for 45 minutes.
Will make 3 regular size pies or 2 deep-dish pies.

title: copper pennies(marinated carrots)
directions: Parboil carrots until tender.
When mixed, place in a bowl and mix in onions and peppers.
Heat sugar and vinegar in saucepan until sugar dissolves.
Add spices, tomato soup and oil slowly. Stir until well blended.
Allow to cool, then pour over vegetables; mix and allow to marinate in refrigerator several days (at least 24 hours).

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook noodles 5 minutes and drain.
In a large skillet, brown meat and onion.
Stir in tomatoes, chili powder and salt.
Heat through.
Combine with noodles.
Put in 3-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple and yam casserole
directions: Combine apple pie filling and sweet potatoes in buttered casserole.
Dot with 3 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg and nuts.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: venison steak
directions: Steak should be at least 1 1/2-inches thick.
Dredge with flour and season with salt and pepper.
Brown in fat on both sides.
Add other ingredients.
Cover tightly and cook in moderate oven (350°) or over low heat on top of stove until tender, about 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sherbet.
As soon as it starts to gel, fold in the drained mandarin oranges and whipped cream.
Pour into a 3 1/2-cup mold and chill.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: mamma's criss cross cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, and egg; add milk and lemon extract. Sift together and stir in, flour, cream of tartar, soda, and salt. Form into quarter size balls. Lay on greased cookie sheet. Dip a fork in sugar and press cookies in a criss cross pattern. You may add nut pieces or cherries on top. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 300°.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: In a large saucepan over medium heat, cook onion and green pepper in margarine.
Add ground chuck and cook until it loses its red color; drain.
Add sugar, salt and black pepper.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: enchilada bake
directions: Combine ingredients in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan or dish. Line with half a package tortilla chips, then place the meat mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with 3/4 cup grated Cheddar cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: stuffed pistolettes
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and seasoning; drain.
Boil broccoli until tender; drain.
Add cheese to meat; stir until melted.
Mix in broccoli.
Cut tops out of rolls; carefully dig out inside. Stuff with meat mixture.
Before baking, brush rolls with garlic butter.
Bake until brown at 350°.
These can be frozen, but do not brush with butter until ready to bake.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Use oyster juice plus enough milk to make 2 cups liquid.
Set aside.
Melt butter and add crumbs and seasonings; toss well to mix.
In a greased casserole dish, alternate layers of oysters and crumb mixture.
Pour liquid over layers and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: golden carrots
directions: Place carrots in a buttered baking dish.
Drain pineapple bits and reserve juice.
Add pineapple to carrots and mix well. Combine
reserved
juice
with brown sugar, tapioca and salt. Stir until dissolved.
Pour over carrot mixture and dot with butter.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Blend eggs; add other ingredients.
Mix until corn is mixed in the batter.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and cook until firm, 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together the pudding and milk for 2 minutes.
Add the sour cream and orange juice.
Drain all juice from fruit and add.
Stir all together.
Chill and serve.

title: marbled pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, creaming well after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Take out 2 cups of cake batter.
Blend cocoa into it.
Alternately spoon light and chocolate batters into lightly greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or a 10-inch Bundt cast aluminum cake pan.
Bake in a slow oven (325°) for 1 hour and 10 minutes for the 10-inch tube pan or 1 hour and 30 minutes for the Bundt pan or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan about 10 minutes.
Invert cake on wire rack and remove pan.
Sift confectioners sugar on cake.

title: oatmeal cookies with filling
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Mix soda and flour.
Add to cream mixture with oatmeal and cinnamon.
Stir in vanilla.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Pinch off walnut size amounts.
Bake 2-inches apart at 350° until barely brown, about 4 to 5 minutes.

title: tangy roast beef pockets
directions: In medium bowl, mix honey, horseradish and mustard; set aside. Divide dough into 8 biscuits.
Roll each biscuit out to 1/8-inch thickness.
On each of 4 biscuits, spread 1/4 of cream cheese, stopping 1/2-inch from edge.
Top each evenly with beef, pimentos and honey-horseradish sauce.
Moisten edge of biscuit with water. Top each with a remaining biscuit and seal edges together by pressing firmly with a fork.
Prick top of each completed pocket a few times with fork.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix melted butter, both cheeses, onion, broccoli and eggs (beaten).
Add cornmeal until thickened.
Pour ingredients into a well-greased skillet.
Bake at 425° for about 30 minutes.

title: corn meal mush
directions: With boiling water, combine in mixing bowl the remaining ingredients.
Gradually add corn meal mixture to boiling water, stirring constantly.
Cool until batter begins to thicken, stirring frequently.
When thick, cover.
Turn heat to very low and cook for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix together cabbage and salt; let stand 1 hour.
Drain water and lift cabbage out.
Boil together rest of ingredients.
Pour over cabbage while hot and let cool.
Put in bags and freeze.

title: coffee punch
directions: Add sugar to hot coffee.
Cool. Spoon ice cream into coffee. Fold in whipped cream.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Put soda in hot water, then combine all other ingredients together.
Add soda and water mixture.
Beat well.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet, usually about 6 to a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 minutes.
Let cool; remove from cookie sheet.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Slightly beat 3 whole eggs. Combine with sugar, blended with cornstarch. Melt butter. Add butter, buttermilk and vanilla. Add a little grated lemon rind. Pour filling into uncooked pie shell. Preheat oven to 400° and then turn oven down to 325°. Bake from 40 to 60 minutes, until filling is set.

title: brandy's dip
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and dill weed in medium bowl. Chill for 2 or 3 hours and serve with chips, vegetables or favorite movie munchies.

title: jello and cottage cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: yugoslavian christmas cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat butter until creamy.
Gradually stir in 1/2 cup sugar and beat until fluffy. Beat in egg yolk and salt.
Stir in flour and mix well.
Pat into greased baking pan.
Beat jelly slightly with fork and spread on dough.
Beat egg whites until foamy; gradually add 1 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat until mixture stands in peaks.
Fold in ground nuts and lemon extract. Swirl over jelly.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix well sugar and syrup.
Microwave 4 minutes on High.
Add peanuts and stir well.
Microwave 3 1/2 minutes on High.
Add butter or oleo and vanilla.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Add baking soda and stir gently.
It will foam up.
Pour on a buttered cookie pan and let cool.
Break up and enjoy.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in 2-quart casserole at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Pour into a greased baking pan (11 x 7 x 2-inch).
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: fresh peach conserve
directions: Use juice of lemon and orange and not the pulp.
Combine all ingredients and cook until thick and clear.
Stir while cooking. Seal in sterilized jars.

title: date nut loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients (save a few crumbs).
Shape into a roll. Wrap in waxed paper and put in refrigerator. Can be handled better if made into 2 rolls, 2 1/2 to 3 inches in diameter.
Slice 3/4-inch thick.
When serving, top with whipped cream, pineapple or lime sherbet.
Roll is sweet and needs something tart.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple. Reserve 6 tablespoons juice. Combine sugar and flour and stir in reserved juice. Add cheese to pineapple chunks, mixing well. Pour mixture in greased casserole dish. Combine melted butter and cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over pineapple mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. This is good with baked ham.

title: pasta al fresco
directions: Cook pasta as package directs; drain.
In large skillet, saute tomatoes, garlic and seasonings in oil 2 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add pasta; toss lightly.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: salmon appetizer spread
directions: Microwave onion and butter on High 30 to 45 seconds or until onion is tender.
Microwave cream cheese on Medium 1 to 1 1/2 minutes until softened.
Stir cream cheese into onion and butter mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into a ball.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Serve with crackers or cocktail bread.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Drain and place broccoli in lightly greased baking dish.
Cube cheese and toss in broccoli.
Mash Ritz crackers and toss through.
Pour into 1/4 cup milk and toss well.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs and dot with margarine.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Pour 1/2 catsup from bottle.
To the catsup left in the bottle, add lemon juice, horseradish, Worcestershire sauce and salt to taste.
Finish filling bottle with vinegar.
Shake well.
Add hot sauce, if desired.
Keep in refrigerator.
Use as needed.
Good on shrimp, oysters and crab.
:5 Carol Taylor

title: zucchini bake
directions: Place zucchini cubes and butter in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cover and cook 5 minutes on High in microwave.
Stir in cheese, seasonings and eggs.
Top with crumbled French fried onions.
Cook at Medium/defrost for 5 minutes, give 1/2 turn and cook 5 more minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Cut each potato lengthwise into eighths.
Put next 4 ingredients into plastic bag.
Add potatoes and shake well. Arrange coated potatoes on shallow pan.
Bake at 375° until tender inside and crusty outside, about 1 hour.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and basil.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix the first four ingredients together, then add the other ingredients. Mix well and place in spoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake at 350 until light brown in color.

title: rotel chicken
directions: In baking dish, cut up chicken and place in bottom.
Mix together soup, onions and Ro-Tel.
Place cut up cheese over chicken.
Break chips and place over cheese.
Pour soup mixture over chips.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, about 20 minutes.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Break up lettuce; place in a bowl with onion.
Crisp the bacon and drain; add to lettuce.
Combine vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and water in a skillet.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Pour over salad.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger baked beans casserole
directions: In a pan, brown meat; pour off excess fat.
Set aside.
Mix the remaining ingredients in a casserole dish.
Stir together. Then add the meat; stir it up also.
Bake in the oven (uncovered) for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese potato soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Add carrots, celery and onion.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add potatoes and cook 20 minutes more.
Check vegetables to see if they are done.
Add soup and mix well.
Add cheese (in pieces).
Cook until cheese is melted. Serve with crumbled bacon on top.
Serves 8.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cube squash and boil until tender.
Drain and mash. Add all ingredients together except half of the butter to the squash. Melt remaining butter. Pour mixture into baking dish and pour melted butter over top.
Sprinkle with additional cracker crumbs until covered. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Half recipe is plenty for 4 people.

title: fruit slaw
directions: Drain pineapple chunks, reserving 2 tablespoons juice.
Set juice aside.

title: sweet marinated slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, green pepper and onions with 1 cup sugar in bowl; mix well.
Combine oil, vinegar, 4 teaspoons sugar, celery seed and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring to mix well. Pour over cabbage mixture; mix well.
Spoon into airtight container.
Chill for 4 hours or longer.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix together sugar, butter and eggs.
Use a small bowl and make a paste with cocoa, vanilla, salt and food coloring.
Add to the first mixture.
Add buttermilk and flour.
Mix well.
Fold in baking soda and vinegar.
Don't beat!
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Cook butter and flour together on low heat, about 10 minutes. Add salt, milk and cheese.
Stir continuously and keep on low heat until cheese melts.
Pour over macaroni, broccoli or anything you want to serve with cheese sauce.

title: carrot-cottage cheese casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake 1 hour in moderate oven.

title: vegetable hamburger stew
directions: Cook for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook green beans, lima beans and peas according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients except crackers and butter and pour into buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt butter.
Crumble Ritz crackers and mix with melted butter.
Top vegetable mixture. Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: potato-stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut a thin slice off tops of tomatoes.
Scoop out insides and turn upside down to drain.
Scrub potatoes well; cook in 1-inch boiling, salted water 35 to 40 minutes or until tender.
Drain; peel.

title: tea cakes
directions: Beat butter, add sugar, eggs and flavoring; sift flour and baking powder.
Add flour until mixer can't go.
Use flour for rolling cookies.
You should have flour left over when finished. Roll very thin and cut with round cutter.
Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 10 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: ruby's cola cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa and soda in bowl.
Add buttermilk, oleo, Cola and vanilla.
Beat on low until all is combined, then medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and beat 2 minutes more. Stir in marshmallows.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together.
Store in airtight container.
Use 1/3 cup mix for 6 ounce cup of hot chocolate.

title: tortilla and black bean casserole(serves 10)
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and ground beef.
Drain.
Add undrained tomatoes, picante sauce, garlic and cumin.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in beans. Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with vegetable spray.
Spread 1/3 of bean mixture on bottom.
Top with half of tortillas, then 1/3 of cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with beans on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes after sprinkling with remaining cheese.
If desired, top with tomato slices, shredded lettuce, sliced green onions, sliced black olives, low-fat sour cream and/or hot sauce.

title: lemon-asparagus pilaf(makes 6 servings)
directions: Chop onion.
Trim asparagus.
Melt butter with oil over medium heat.
Add onion and cook until soft.
Stir in asparagus and thyme and cook about 1 minute.
Add the rice and cook, stirring about 1 minute.
Add chicken stock and water.
Cover and bring to a simmer. Reduce heat and cook rice about 20 to 25 minutes.
Grate the colored zest from the lemon and squeeze 1 tablespoon juice.
Stir in the zest and juice just before serving.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a pan melt butter and sprinkle crumbs together; firmly press down in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle chocolate morsels and nuts.
Pour milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: my best gingerbread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg and molasses, then the dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Add hot water last and beat until smooth.
The batter is soft, but it makes a fine cake.
Bake in greased pan for 35 minutes at 350°. Makes 15 generous servings.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix together. Chill and serve.

title: turketti
directions: Cook spaghetti as usual.
Mix all ingredients in large casserole, retaining enough cheese to cover top.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Add remaining cheese to top and return to heat just long enough to melt cheese.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Oil a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cube bread and line dish with bread.
Top with crumbled sausage, cheeses and sliced mushrooms. To beaten eggs, add cream, milk and seasonings.
Pour over casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza
directions: Put sauce on crust.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put cheese last.
Cook until done, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown meat and drain off grease.
Stir in barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Grease a muffin pan with shortening and press a biscuit into each cup of muffin pan.
Spoon beef mixture into cups and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Preheat oven to 400° and bake 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: sugar nut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, water and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Make into rolls about 1-inch in diameter; roll in plastic wrap and freeze.
Slice 1/4-inch thick and bake at 400° on an ungreased cookie sheet for about 15 minutes.

title: gram's chocolate pudding
directions: Cook until thick and smooth.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Cook
first
3 ingredients until thick and brown.
(The browner
it
is
the more butterscotch taste it has.) Then mix last
ingredients
together.
Add to first mixture and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: baked chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 9 x 13-inch baking dish with foil. Combine first 4 ingredients in shallow dish and mix thoroughly. Melt butter in saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add garlic and saute about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Dip chicken in this mixture and then in bread crumbs, coating well.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onions together until meat has lost pink color, keeping separated as cooking. Cook noodles in salted water until tender; drain. Mix all ingredients together; put into a 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole. Cover with buttered crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: upside-down chili pie
directions: Brown meat in oil in iron skillet.
Add next 8 ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Make cornbread mix and add creamed corn.
Put on top of meat mixture.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 minutes.
Turn over on large platter or cookie sheet.
The meat will be on top.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and parsley.

title: hot cranberry tea
directions: Melt red hots in water.
Add all ingredients and bring to a boil in large pot.
Simmer 5 minutes or longer to blend.

title: little cheese tarts
directions: Put paper liners in cupcake pans and place a wafer/cookie in bottom of each liner.
Beat remaining ingredients until light and fluffy.
Pour in cupcake pans, filling each about 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
As soon as removed from oven, put one tablespoon of canned pie filling on top of each tart.
Makes about 24.
Store covered in fridge.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli with onion.
Drain thoroughly.
Place in casserole with other ingredients.
Top with crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: veggies and polish sausage
directions: In large skillet put butter and water.
Add broccoli, cauliflower, potatoes, carrots and onion; cook until tender.
Cut smoked sausage into 1-inch pieces.
Lay on top of veggies and cook 10 minutes or put in microwave for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: hershey pie
directions: Melt together first three ingredients.
Whip whipping cream; add to mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate. Top with Cool Whip.

title: sweet and sour spread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Chill, pour over cream cheese and serve with crackers.

title: party sausage balls
directions: Combine in mixing bowl the sausage, cheese and Bisquick.
Add just enough water to shape in small balls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: miniature cheese cakes
directions: Mix
cream
cheese,
sugar and egg yolks and set aside. Beat egg
whites
and fold into cream cheese mixture.
Grease miniature muffin pan and sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs. Spoon
about one
tablespoon of the cream cheese mixture into muffin
pan. Bake
at
for
15 minutes.
Allow to cool. When cool, a dip will form in the center of each cheese cake.

title: yogurt fruit salad
directions: Sprinkle with cinnamon and then mix well.
This is a terrific after school treat.

title: lassie's favorite treats
directions: In
large bowl pour hot water over
oatmeal,
margarine and bouillon granules; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir
in powdered milk, cornmeal and egg.
Add flour, 1/2 cup at a	time, mixing well after each addition.
Knead 3 to 4 minutes,
adding
more flour if needed to make a very stiff dough.	Pat or	roll
out dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into shapes with dog biscuit or
other cookie cutter and place on a greased
cookie
sheet. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Allow to cool and dry
out until hard.
Makes about 1 3/4 pounds.

title: sunday breakfast casserole
directions: Fry sausage and drain.
Place bread crumbs into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Layer half sausage, half cheese; repeat.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour over sausage and cheese mixture. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: In large bowl combine egg, water, salad dressing mix and seasoning blend.
Stir in Chex to moisten.
Let stand 5 minutes. Stir to break up Chex.
Add ground beef and celery.
Mix well. Shape into loaf in shallow pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 70 minutes. Top with cheese strips 5 minutes before end of baking.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: alma's sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift the flour over the potatoes, starting with 1 1/2 cups. Cut butter into the flour and potato mixture. Add sugar and milk. If dough is too soft, add more flour. Knead, roll and cut with large biscuit cutter. Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Put ribs in a roasting pan.
Place a slice of onion on each piece (or chop onion and add to ribs).
Roast at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: saint frances chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Drain and layer cut-up chicken in bottom of baking dish.
In saucepan melt butter and add flour and salt until bubbly.
Then add chicken broth, cream of chicken soup and chilies until thickened.
Remove from heat and add room temperature sour cream.
Pour warm sauce over chicken and top with shredded cheese.
Place in oven at 350° and cook for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown meat in oil in frying pan.
Add chopped vegetables, salt and pepper and stir-fry for another 5 minutes or so.
Mix in 3/4 can of tomato sauce, reserving 1/4 can for topping.
Add enough water to keep from sticking.
Cover and cook over low heat 1/2 hour, stirring frequently.

title: chicken oriental
directions: Saute chicken, garlic, pepper and carrot, then add everything, except rice.
Bring to a full boil, then stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix pie filling and beaten egg together.
Dump into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump remaining ingredients into pan in order, spreading or sprinkling them on evenly.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: "dirt"
directions: Mix together margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
In separate bowl mix together pudding, milk and vanilla; then combine both mixtures.
Add Cool Whip.

title: mexican bean hot pot
directions: Cover beans with water and let stand overnight; drain. Brown sausage in Dutch oven. Add onions; cook and stir until tender. Add remaining ingredients, except chilies. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 2 hours or until tender. Stir in chilies; heat through. Makes about 3 quarts.

title: pasta with garlic and olive
directions: While water is heating for pasta, add all ingredients except cheese to pan and saute over medium heat until garlic is translucent. Reduce heat to very low. Cook pasta; drain and put in serving bowl. Add sauce; stir. Sprinkle liberally with cheese and serve. Add fresh ground black pepper to taste.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Cook hamburg.
Add to other ingredients.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Mix with spaghetti sauce and cottage cheese.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Grease pan and pour in 1/2 cup of sauce, then 1 layer of noodles, sauce and cheese; repeat layers.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake for 15 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Stir in melted chocolate, vanilla and flour.
Blend well; stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for about 35 minutes.

title: grilled barbecue shrimp
directions: Put shrimp on skewers suitable for grilling.
Baste with sauce and let sit until grill is very hot.
Grill approximately 5 to 10 minutes on each side or until done.
Baste often.
Enjoy!
Serves 4.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in shortening in heavy skillet.
Add onion, tomatoes, catsup, sauce and pepper.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Add to casserole.
Put all ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Fold in soup; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: cranberry-orange nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together flours, baking powder, soda and sugar.
Beat margarine, orange juice and rind into egg. Stir into flour mixture.
Add cranberries and nuts.
Pour into an 8-cup loaf or ring pan, greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Fry hash browns and crumble up.
Add chopped green pepper and onion.
Mix together.
Add melted cheese and mix.
Pour more cheese on top. Add bacon bits on top.
Better if served hot.

title: baked stuffed peppers
directions: Brown ground beef in oil.
Add chopped onion and cook until onion are tender. Add seasoning, stir in drained, partially cooked rice and remove from fire.
Fill raw peppers with meat mixture. Place in baking dish deep enough so peppers won't turn over.
Pour tomato sauce over tops.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour.

title: spinach chicken quiche
directions: Cut leek in half lengthwise, wash and trim, leaving green tops intact.
Cut crosswise into thin slices.
Place leek in small saucepan.
Add enough water to cover.
Cook until boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: braunschweiger ball
directions: Mix all together, except pecans.
Form into ball; roll in chopped nuts.
Yields 3 cups.

title: easy mexican meatballs
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine all ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Microwave for 3 minutes; cover with wax paper or bake at 300° until done.

title: cameo cake
directions: Combine butter and water in medium saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add white chocolate, stirring until chocolate melts.
Stir in buttermilk, eggs and vanilla; set aside.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup flour and pecans, stirring to coat; set aside.
Combine remaining 3 cups flour, sugar and soda in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually stir in white chocolate mixture.
Fold in pecan mixture (batter will be thin).
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans on wire racks 10 minutes; remove from pans and let cool completely on wire racks.
Spread White Chocolate Cream Cheese Frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 3 cups of boiling hot water.
Add cranberries and stir to mix.
Add the rest of the ingredients and put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cut top of beets off.
Wash and cook in cold pack canner.
Let water come up over beets.
Cook until tender and peel.
Make a mixture of vinegar and water.
May need several cups of vinegar and water, according to amount of beets.
Sweeten to taste.
Pour over beets; bring to a boil.
Put in jars.
Pour mixture over beets and seal.

title: chicken-cheese lasagne
directions: Heat oleo in 2-quart pan until melted.
Add garlic.
Stir in flour and salt.
Cook, stirring, until it bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk and broth.
Heat to boiling (1 minute).
Stir in Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese, onion, basil, oregano and pepper.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted.

title: party chicken
directions: Line glass baking dish with pressed beef.
Place chicken breasts on beef with a slice of bacon on each breast.
Thoroughly mix sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serves 8.

title: irish brown bread
directions: Blend sugar and water, cook three minutes.
Add raisins and simmer for 3 minutes.
Add margarine and let cool.
Mix flour, spices and baking soda together.
Blend into raisin mixture. Pour into buttered pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: holy smoke
directions: Mix flour, pecans and butter.
Line a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Put in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Mix Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Pour over the crust. Prepare pudding according to directions.
Spread over the top. Top with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: kool-aid sherbet
directions: Dissolve sugar and Kool-Aid in milk.
Pour into freezer tray, until mushy.
Spoon into mixer bowl, beat until smooth.
Return to freezer tray for about 2 hours.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: crock-pot chicken soup
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low all day. Remove chicken bones.
Serve plain or over noodles or rice. Great for a working Mom.

title: low calorie herb dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium bowl and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with assorted crudites.

title: pineapple banana pie
directions: Cut bananas into slices and layer in pie crust.
Then over low heat, combine pineapple, sugar and flour into medium saucepan until thick.
Let cool, then layer over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar and continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in flour and lemon juice.
Spread batter into well-greased 10 x 15-inch jellyroll pan.
With a knife, mark off dough into 20 squares.
Place 1 heaping tablespoonful pie filling in center of each square.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix the cheese, chili and picante sauce.
While cheese is melting, add hamburger.
Heat in crock-pot on low.
Serve with chips.

title: rican rice and beans
directions: Cook beans without salt or grease.
Chop onions, peppers, tomatoes and garlic.
Then saute in bacon grease for about 20 minutes.
Add ham, tomato paste and sauteed ingredients to beans and cook for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.
Serves 8.

title: tropical swamp cooler(kid's favorites)
directions: In pitcher, combine puree and orange juice.
Just before serving, add soda water.
Place ice in glasses.
Fill with Tropical Swamp Cooler. Serve with straws, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: clam dip
directions: Add Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice to the drained clams and blend into softened cream cheese.
Chill and serve with chips or vegetable dippers.
Can be diluted with cream for easier dipping.

title: surprise casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a covered greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal and peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and salt in saucepan.
Stir; bring to a full boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter; stir until smooth.
Add rolled oats; mix well.
Cool slightly, until mixture holds its shape slightly.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool.
Makes about 4 dozen clusters.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Put
chicken
in oven and bake until done.
In a saucepan, mix
garlic
salt,	parsley
flakes, can of tomatoes and Parmesan cheese.
Pour
over chicken. Slice tomato and lay on top
of chicken.
Put Mozzarella cheese over tomato and chicken.
Place back in oven for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve.

title: heavenly hamburger
directions: Melt shortening and brown meat slightly in skillet.
Season with onion salt, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients, in layers, in order given.
Rinse tomato can with water and pour over ingredients.
Cover.

title: bear biscuits
directions: Separate 4 biscuits into eighths.
Leave 6 biscuits whole. Round small dough pieces into small ears and nose.
Press firmly into whole biscuits.
Press raisins into face for eyes and end of nose.
Add 1/4 of cherry to each ear.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 400° until golden brown.
Enjoy with honey of course!

title: sweet - sour meatballs
directions: Combine ground chuck, bread crumbs or oats, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in a single or double layer in baking pan.
Set aside.
In another bowl, combine tomato sauce, catsup and sugar.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over noodles or in a chafing dish as an appetizer.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in Tupperware container.

title: batter dipped hot dogs
directions: Sift together the meal, flour and salt.
Add milk, egg and oil and beat until smooth.
Dip wieners in batter, holding them with kitchen fork or tongs.
Drain off excess.
Fry in hot oil in skillet (375°) for 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain on absorbent paper. Insert skewers and serve with mustard sauce made by mixing the last 3 ingredients together.

title: j's herb-rice mix
directions: Divide rice and bouillon granules into 4 packages; set aside. Combine remaining ingredients; stir and divide among packages. Seal.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except noodles in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Stir in 1/2 can of chow mein noodles.
Then sprinkle remainder of chow mein noodles over the top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: graham cracker treats
directions: Boil oleo, butter and sugar.
Place graham crackers on foil on cookie sheet.
Pour syrup mixture over graham crackers.
Sprinkle with
nuts.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Remove from cookie sheet while still hot.

title: baked apples
directions: Will use a microwave or campfire and tinfoil (if using campfire).

title: mikey's bread sticks
directions: Into a bowl, put whole wheat flour.
Add salt, honey and cinnamon.
Stir well and add oil and cold water.
(For sesame bread sticks, add 1/2 cup sesame seed.)

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and margarine and press in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes exactly or 350° for 9 minutes. Beat sugar into cream cheese.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled pretzel mixture.
(May thin with small amount milk.) Prepare Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Cool few minutes.
