Add strawberries with juice, stirring to melt.
Mix together and set until it begins to gel.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Refrigerate. Serves 12.

title: cherry-chocolate shake
directions: Stir the chocolate drink into the milk.
Pour into 4 tall glasses.
Add a scoop of ice cream to each.
Fill with club soda and stir until foamy.
Yields 4 glasses.

title: rice casserole deluxe
directions: In country cooker, place margarine.
Add onion, celery and green pepper.
Cook on Full power for 4 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are slightly tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Place top on country cooker.
Cook at Full power for 9 minutes. Stir.
Cook 9 minutes more.
Add salt, if desired.
Serves 8 to 10.
May add bacon crumbles, if desired.

title: cold duck punch
directions: In a large bowl or pitcher, stir together cranberry juice, pineapple and lemonade concentrate.
Cover and chill.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix together well and pour over the vegetables.
Allow to stand 24 hours before serving.

title: chicken salad
directions: Shape into ball and roll in nuts.

title: quick and easy greek lamb casserole
directions: Brown chops in butter or margarine.
Place uncooked rice at bottom of a greased casserole dish.
Layer chops on top.
Place slices of onions, tomatoes and green pepper on top and add salt, pepper and parsley as you do.
Pour broth or consomme around.
Add marjoram and thyme.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: *koulourakia(twist cookie)
directions: Cream butter for about 10 minutes or until light colored.
Add sugar gradually and beat again well. Add eggs, orange juice, vanilla, whiskey and allspice. Continue beating.
Mix baking powder with the first cup of flour. Add flour to the butter mixture.
Continue adding flour until you have a soft dough. Shape into desired designs and twists.
Brush tops with well beaten egg. Sprinkle sesame seed on top and bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by tsp. into hot oil, and cook until golden brown.

title: mother's bread pudding
directions: Crumble up biscuits.
Add all other ingredients except egg. Add the egg after sugar to taste.
Pour into a greased pan.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 325° until a knife doesn't adhere.

title: inside-out tamale pie
directions: Cook rice; set aside and brown hamburger and onion and drain off fat.
Combine hamburger, onion, rice and rest of ingredients. Heat and blend.
Serve with cornbread.

title: heloise's jamaican barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a quart jar.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: cold pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles
and
drain.
Mix with dressing until well moistened. Chill.
Just before serving, add Bac*Os.

title: english trifle
directions: Slice pound cake into thin pieces.
Place in casserole dish. Sprinkle Amaretto on cake, as much or as little as you like.
On top of this spread on some preserves then spread pudding, then spread on whipped cream.
Keep layering ingredients until everything is used up, then top with fresh raspberries. Refrigerate 3 hours to let flavors meld.
Slice and serve.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Heat buttermilk to lukewarm.
Add soda, sugar, salt and shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add first mixture to yeast paste.
Add 5 to 6 cups flour.
Turn out on floured board and knead until smooth.
Cover with cloth and let rest on board 10 to 15 minutes.
Make into rolls.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: pineapple cheesecake(dietetic)
directions: Place drained pineapple in blender with half of its juice. Add gelatin and hot water; blend 2 minutes.
Add dry milk and remainder of juice, sweetener, flavorings and lemon juice.
Blend for 3 minutes.
Pour into a 10-inch pan, sprinkle lightly with cinnamon and allow to set for 1 hour.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut beef into very thin strips and brown in hot oil.
Add garlic and cook until yellow.
Add soy sauce, salt and 1/3 cup water.
Cook on low heat for 45 minutes.
Add vegetables and cook 10 minutes.
Blend cornstarch with 1 cup cold water; add and stir into beef mixture.
Add tomatoes and cook 5 minutes.
Serve over hot, fluffy rice.
Serves 6.
Suitable for freezing.

title: fudge
directions: Cook sugar, Pet milk and butter 10 minutes after boiling starts, stirring consistently.
Add chocolate chips, marshmallow cream, vanilla and nuts.
Stir and pour into buttered pan.

title: broken glass torte
directions: Prepare the 3 packages gelatin separately, using 1 cup hot water and 1/2 cup cold water per package.
Pour into separate pans.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onions and peppers in shortening until tender.
Add ground meat.
Add tomatoes, rice and seasonings.
Arrange in a large greased casserole, cover and bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften at room temperature.
In a small bowl, beat the cheese until fluffy.
Add the syrup and continue to beat.
Add the peanut butter and mix well.	Excellent on banana cake.

title: italian salad
directions: Use a large, chilled bowl.
Break lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Add cucumbers and mushrooms.
When ready to serve, add cheese and parsley and pour on dressing.
Toss and serve at once.

title: twice baked potato casserole
directions: Cut baked potatoes into 1 inch cubes and place half in a greased 13 X 9 X 2

inch baking dish. Sprinkle with half of sour cream and half of both cheeses. Repeat Layers. Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted. Sprinkle with chopped green onions and pimentos.

title: cream lefse(rommebro)
directions: Use enough flour to roll out and bake on lefse plate at medium heat.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Slowly add sugar while beating at high speed.
Continue beating for 5 minutes.
Carefully fold in M&M's and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on aluminum foil-covered cookie sheet. Place in preheated oven and turn off the heat.
Leave in oven overnight.
Do not open oven door until morning.

title: peach cobbler pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except pie shells.
Blend well until mixture forms a batter. Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes or until firm.

title: brownies
directions: Grease pan or Pyrex dish.
Cream the butter, sugar and eggs; add next 4 ingredients.
Bake in 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Test for doneness with toothpick.
While still hot, sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut in squares.

title: masako's bean bake
directions: Drain the lima and kidney beans.
Combine with pork and beans. Saute the chopped onion in the bacon drippings.
Add the bacon and onion to the beans with the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Put chicken with broth, beef, tomato juice and butter beans (bring to boil in separate pot barely covered in water).
Add all of above together in large pot.
Cook for about 2 hours, then add corn, diced potatoes (which have been brought to boil in water in separate pot).
Add to large pot.
Cook another 2 hours until very thick!

title: chicken and rice
directions: Empty rice and seasoning packet into baking dish. Mix soup with a can of water.
Put chicken on top of rice and pour soup mixture over all.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Mix all ingredients except for kisses. Roll into balls and press down with a fork. Press a Hershey kiss in the middle. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: puff pancake
directions: Melt butter in 9-inch pie pan, preferably Pyrex.
Mix flour, milk, eggs and nutmeg.
Pour batter into hot, melted butter in pie pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, lemon juice and fruit or serve with syrup.
Serve immediately. Serves 2 or 3.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Generously grease bottom only of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Sprinkle marshmallows evenly over bottom of pan.

title: good cheese roll
directions: Mix all together and roll in chopped pecans.
Chill and cut in slices.

title: marshmallow popcorn balls
directions: Separate unpopped kernels from popcorn.
Melt margarine in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted and well blended.
Remove from heat.
Pour over popcorn. Mix well with a spoon.
Grease hands with butter and shape popcorn into balls.
Let stand on wax paper or greased foil.
Makes about 10 balls.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk.
Cook until it makes a string, then add remaining ingredients.
Spoon onto foil or wax paper to cool.

title: summer smoothe
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container. Blend until smooth.
Serve at once.
If you aren't using a blender, mash fruit in a bowl.
Put fruit, crushed ice, yogurt and juice in a jar. Cover tightly and shake for 30 seconds until a minute. Makes 3 medium servings.

title: zippy stuffed franks
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
In medium mixing bowl, combine crushed herb stuffing mix, onion, catsup, pickle relish and water.
Cut franks lengthwise almost to opposite side.
Mound stuffing mixture in franks.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Place cheese strips atop.
Return to oven; bake 3 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: sour cream spice cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add egg and beat well. Add sour cream and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add gradually to sugar mixture, stirring well.
Bake in a loaf pan in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Can add raisins or nuts.

title: p.t.a. broccoli quiche
directions: Follow directions on pie shell to pre-bake.
Set aside.

title: beer beef roll
directions: Roll steak and place on heavy foil on cookie sheet.
Puncture the meat roll.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour mixture over meat.
Roll up foil tightly around meat and beer mixture.
Bake at 350° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: caramel custard
directions: Brown sugar in a skillet; add 1/2 cup water.
Pour in a baking dish.
Beat eggs, cream and scalded milk.
Pour over sugar.
Sit in pan of water and bake slowly until a knife comes out clean. Sprinkle top with nutmeg.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all together with spoon or fork, adding blueberries last. Do not overbeat.
Pour into muffin tins and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chili dip
directions: Pour chili into slow cooker.
Cut cream cheese into chunks and add to chili.
Add shredded cheese.
Stir well.
Cover.
Cook on low 4 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and drain. Add seasoning packages. Dump cans into large pan. Cook 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt miniature marshmallows in milk; cool.
Whip cream; add vanilla.
Add grated chocolate; add this to milk mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust; chill in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, margarine, peanut butter, sugar and egg. Blend in flour. Cover and chill. Heat oven to 375 degrees. Shape dough into 1 inch balls. Place 3 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet. With fork dipped in flour, flatten in crisscross pattern to 2 inches. Bake 10 -12 minutes or until set but not hard. Makes approx. 3 dozen.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter, beating until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and lemon, mixing well.
Gently stir in 7-Up.
Pour into well greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until tests done.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Add macaroni.
Stir until well coated.
Add salt, pepper and cheese.
Pour milk over mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Place pretzels in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients; coat pretzels with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, stirring gently after 5 minutes.
Cool and store in an airtight container.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Combine other ingredients; stir into sausage mixture.
Serve over rice.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Cut fat from pork chops.
Dredge in mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Brown on both sides in skillet with butter.
Remove from skillet and place in a 2-quart casserole.
Empty soup in skillet, stirring well.
Add water and heat.
Pour over pork chops.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour or until tender.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix Crisco, brown sugar and white sugar. Add eggs and mix again.
Add dry ingredients.
Add chocolate chips. Drop by spoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: cookies oatmeal krispies
directions: Thoroughly cream (with a fork) 1 cup of lard with the butter. Add white sugar and brown sugar.
Add the unbeaten eggs and vanilla extract; beat tolerably well.
Add the flour, salt and baking soda to the blended ingredients.
Spoon into this mixture the rolled oats and nut meats or raisins (optional).
Use your hands to work all the ingredients together, then roll into a log. Wrap in a wet towel; chill as much as possible.
Slice thin and bake on greased sheets until a light brown.

title: chinese chicken dinner
directions: Skin, bone and cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Saute first 4 ingredients in hot oil 5 minutes.
Remove from skillet.
Saute chicken until tender.
Combine cornstarch, soy sauce and broth. Add to chicken and stir until begins to bubble.
Cook 1 minute; add vegetables and meat.
Serve over rice.

title: taco bake
directions: Season and brown ground beef. Add green peppers and onions. Set this aside.

title: pampered chicken
directions: Sprinkle the chicken with salt and pepper.
Heat the oil and butter in a heavy skillet.
Add the chicken breasts and saute over medium-high heat until lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Add the shallots and garlic around the chicken and cook briefly.
Add the tarragon, tomatoes, vinegar, capers, wine and tomato paste. Stir and blend well; bring to a boil, cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: deer jerky
directions: Cut meat into desired thickness.
Mix remaining ingredients and cover meat with marinade overnight.
Hang in oven on toothpicks.
Set oven as low as possible.
Cook 6 to 10 hours.
If it appears dry, it is done.
If it looks wet, cook longer.

title: pork loin
directions: Put all in crockpot and cook all day.
Five minutes before serving add one small can green chilies.
Serve on rolls or as a filling in tortillas.

title: whipped cream icing
directions: Cook flour and milk to form a paste.
Let cool.
Cream butter and shortening for 4 minutes.
Add sugar and beat 4 minutes.
Add paste and vanilla and beat 4 minutes.
Refrigerate.

title: great instant tea
directions: In tea
pitcher,
mix
Sweet 'N Low, tea and hot water; let stand,
if
possible,
for at least 5 to 15 minutes.
Fill pitcher with cold water.
Mix thoroughly.
Double for 1 gallon tea pitcher.
Pour over ice in glasses and serve.

title: ranch snack crackers
directions: Combine oil, garlic powder, dill weed and dressing mix. Pour over crackers (popcorn) stir until all are coated.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Brown sausage or bacon in skillet, stirring, until crumbly.
Drain well.
Crumble bread slices in bottom of dish.
Top with browned sausage or bacon.
Combine eggs, milk and mustard.
Sprinkle grated cheese over sausage or bacon layer.
Pour egg mixture over cheese layer. Let stand 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes. (May be made the night before, refrigerated and baked the next morning.)

title: marinated cole slaw
directions: Put sugar, oil and vinegar in saucepan; bring to boil and set aside to cool.
Toss all ingredients together and pour cooled liquid over cabbage; toss again.
Season to taste with celery salt, salt and pepper.
Marinate overnight in covered bowl.
The men love this dish!

title: lasagna
directions: Boil lasagna until done. Cook Hamburger meat and onions until onions are tender and meat is browned. Drain. Add Ragu. Layer lasagna noodles, meat mixture, cottage cheese, cheddar cheese, and mozzarella cheese. Repeat. Top with parmesan cheese, if desired. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Spread bean dip on bottom of dish.
Mash avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper together to make guacamole.
Spread over bean dip.
Combine sour cream, taco seasoning and mayonnaise. Spread over guacamole.
Top with green onions, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix as other cakes.
Start in a cold oven.
Bake at 300°.

title: chafing dish meat balls(make 2 days in advance)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and shape into 1-inch balls.
Simmer until brown in last 3 ingredients.
Prepare 2 days in advance. Refrigerate, then remove all grease from top.
Reheat and serve in chafing dish.
May be frozen.
Serves 50 to 60.

title: sunny spinach salad
directions: Combine ingredients. Good served with vinaigrette dressing. Serves 8 to 10.

title: gazpacho(no-cook soup)
directions: Chop tomatoes.
Combine tomatoes, cucumber, green pepper and green onions.
Stir in vegetable juice, vinegar, oil, garlic, salt, basil and hot pepper sauce.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: hearty oatmeal muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease bottoms of 12 muffin cups or use paper liners. Combine pancake mix, oats, brown sugar and cinnamon. Add remaining ingredients; mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill cups 3/4 full. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: creamed cheese lemon bar cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and egg with fork until thoroughly moistened.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan or Pyrex dish.
Grease the bottom of the pan only.
Mix frosting and cream cheese together and set aside 1/2 cup for frosting the cooled cake.
To the balance of mixture, add 2 eggs.
Mix well and pour over first layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool thoroughly and frost with reserved frosting.
Cut into small squares.

title: pear relish
directions: Peel and thinly slice the onion into rings.
Cover with cold water and soak for 30 minutes.
Drain.
In a small bowl (ceramic, not plastic, which will hold the smell forever), stir the sugar into the vinegar until dissolved.
Add the drained onion.
Cover tightly with foil and refrigerate for a few hours, stirring once or twice and pushing the onion rings under the vinegar.
Use for salads and any dish requiring raw onion.

title: white bean chili
directions: Soak beans overnight. Drain in a large dutch oven, add beans, chicken broth, garlic, and half of the chopped onions. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 3 hours. Saute remaining onions in oil. Add chilies, spices and diced chicken. Saute for 5 minutes. Add this mixture to the beans and continue to simmer for an additional hour. Serve topped with cheese.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Cut bread into 1 inch cubes. Set aside. Combine cheddar cheese, cream cheese and butter in the top of a double boiler. Cook over boiling water until cheese melts, stirring frequently. Add worcestershire sauce, mustard, Old Bay seasoning and garlic; stir well. Remove cheese mixture from heat. Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form. Gently fold into cheese mixture. Dip bread cubes into cheese mixture, coating well. Place cubes on a greased baking sheet and freeze 1 hour. (Recipe can be made to this point up to 1 month ahead. When cubes are completely frozen, transfer to freezer bags for easier storage. Do not thaw. Bake on greased baking sheets as directed.) Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve hot.

title: pennsylvania dutch funnel cakes
directions: Heat 3/4-inch salad oil to 325° in skillet or electric skillet.
Mix first 6 ingredients with a fork in a bowl.
Pour 1/4 cup batter from a funnel (close spout with finger) or use a teapot.
Make a spiral 6-inch in diameter in hot oil. Fry for 3 to 5 minutes, turning once.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Makes 7. Serve warm.

title: escalloped cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling salted water for a few minutes.
In medium bowl, mix milk, butter and flour.
Stir cooked and drained cabbage into sauce.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: hamburger sauce
directions: Mix together first 4 items.
Add water to make 1 cup.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; boil 1 minute.
Stir in the peanut butter and oatmeal.
Add the vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: apple raisin bran muffins
directions: Beat eggs; add milk to make 1 1/2 cups. Add Raisin Bran and allow to soak. Combine dry ingredients; cut in butter.
Dice apples and combine all ingredients. Pour into muffin tins. Bake 20 minutes at 400°. Makes 12 muffins.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Add optional items.
Pour batter into two greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: air cake
directions: Put egg yolks into mixing bowl.
Beat at low speed 2 minutes. Add water and beat until foams like whites.
Add small amounts of sugar at a time, beating 4 minutes.
Add flavoring, flour with cream of tartar, beating in small amounts at a time.
Beat for 4 minutes.
Add pinch of salt to egg whites.
Beat until dry.
Fold into mixture.

title: slushy punch
directions: Boil sugar and water for 3 minutes.
Add jello; mix until dissolved.
Add juices.
Stir and freeze (in plastic ice cream bucket).
Set out 2 hours before serving in bowl.
Add 2 large bottles ginger ale.
Makes 2 large punch bowls full.

title: barbecues
directions: Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add 1 pound chipped ham.
Cut the ham into small pieces.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soak all of the above in cream about 5 minutes.
Saute the onion and make your meatballs.
Brown the meatballs in 2 Tbsp. of butter in skillet with drippings.
Stir in 2 Tbsp of flour. Dissolve 1 beef bouillon in 1/14 c. of boiling water with 1/2 tsp. of coffee powder.
Add everything together and cook until thickened.

title: mousse
directions: Prepare pudding; let set for 3 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip. Use less Cool Whip if too rich.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut margarine into cake mix until crumbly. Mix in coconut.
Pat into ungreased oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inches).
Build up edges.
Bake 10 minutes.
Arrange apple slices on warm crust.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on apples. Blend sour cream and egg; drizzle over apples. Bake 25 minutes or until edges are light brown.
(You can substitute large can of peaches or pears.)

title: jamaican jerk chicken
directions: In small bowl, combine scallions, garlic, ginger and chile.

title: oriental soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in water and simmer spinach or watercress just until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 2 more minutes.
Serves 5 generously.

title: spinach dip
directions: Serve with pumpernickel bread or party rye.

title: molasses thumbprint cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Add molasses and sifted dry ingredients.
Roll into little balls and roll in sugar.
Make thumbprint in center and fill hole with raspberry jam.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: herbed salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in jar.
Shake well.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar and water.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Stir into brown sugar mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with chocolate bits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix crumbs and baking powder well. Add all other ingredients and mix well. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: barb's christmas brunch quiche
directions: Mix eggs, mayonnaise, milk and flour.
Add onions, Cheddar cheese and broccoli.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: gracia yingst's pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add beaten egg.
Blend in vanilla and pumpkin.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to pumpkin mixture.
Fold in chopped walnuts.
Drop dough by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: the great pumpkin loaf
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until well blended.
Mix in pumpkin.
In another bowl, combine all 7 ingredients.
Stir until well mixed. Pour, all at once, over batter.
Stir just enough to moisten. Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes, or until done.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove to rack to finish cooling.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix together well all of the ingredients except the crabmeat. Then pour mixture over the crabmeat and fold in lightly but thoroughly.
Form into six cakes.
Cook cakes in frying pan in just enough oil to prevent sticking, until browned, about 5 minutes on each side.

title: mom's chocolate cake
directions: Boil water, butter and chocolate.
Set aside to cool.
Mix sugar, flour, baking soda, eggs and sour cream.
Mix in chocolate mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking pan and bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: mary's beef and rice
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Drain.
Add rice, water, onions, celery and mushrooms with liquid and tomatoes with liquid.
Add green pepper, salt and black pepper.
Stir and mix well.
Simmer until rice is tender, stirring occasionally.
Cook about 30 minutes.
May have to add more water if mixture is dry.

title: lo-cal, low-fat hot dog stir-fry
directions: Spray skillet or wok with Pam.
Heat 1 teaspoon oil (canola or safflower) in wok or skillet.
Add sliced potatoes, raw vegetables and 2 sliced hot dogs, stir-frying until vegetables and potatoes are tender but not soft.
Sprinkle with Creole seasoning or light soy sauce.
Serves 1.
Double portions to serve 2.

title: sausage balls
directions: Knead until mixed well. Roll in balls. Bake until browned at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: 1888 recipe gingersnaps
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed.
Add enough flour and mix hard.
Roll thin.
Cut and bake in hot oven.
Preheat at 375°.

title: stuffed sweet italian peppers
directions: Cut tops of peppers off, rinse out seeds. Cook rice and bacon. Add oregano, pepper, parmasen cheese, eggs, parsley and munster cheese. Mix well and stuff peppers. Place in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 min. until peppers are soft.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put 3 cups strawberries in 9-inch baked pie shell.
Crush 1 cup berries and add 1/2 cup water; bring to boil.
Cook 3 minutes, then add 1 cup sugar and boil another 3 minutes.
Add cornstarch, dissolved in water, and boil 3 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Stir occasionally.
When cool, put in pie shell and chill.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: spinach cheese bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Mix all ingredients, except spinach, until well blended.
Beat 1 minute.
Stir in spinach until well blended.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden toothpick in center comes out clean, 55 to 65 minutes. Remove from pan.

title: linguini with clam sauce
directions: Coat a large saucepan with cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add onion, celery and garlic; saute until tender. Drain clams, reserving liquid; add clam liquid, tomatoes, basil, oregano and hot sauce to saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Stir in clams and parsley; cook until thoroughly heated.
Serve over linguini.
Yields 4 servings (about 128 calories per serving plus 90 calories per 1/2 cup cooked linguini).

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing as directed on box.
Place in bottom of 2 quart casserole dish. Put chicken pieces on top of stuffing and undiluted soup on top of chicken.
Next, layer thawed broccoli on top of soup.
Sprinkle the grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes uncovered.
Let set for 10 minutes before serving.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake for 2 hours at 300°.

title: chili cheese squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together.
Chill 1 hour.
For lower calorie, I use lite fruit cocktail and sugar-free pudding.

title: fluffy cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Refrigerate. Delicious!!

title: malasadas
directions: Dissolve yeast and the 1 teaspoon sugar in warm water.
Beat eggs very well.
Measure flour, 1/2 cup sugar and salt into large bowl; make a well and add yeast, eggs, milk, water and butter. Beat well to form soft smooth dough.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
With a circular motion following edge of bowl, turn dough and let rise until doubled.
Heat deep fat to 375°.
Spoon teaspoonfuls of dough carefully from bowl to keep risen dough from falling.
Drop into fat and fry until brown.
Drain on paper towels; shake in bag with sugar.
Serve hot.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into a well-greased loaf pan. Bake at 300° for 70 to 90 minutes.
Can use with ice cream or whipped cream.
Can also freeze.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Bake cake in a greased and floured 11 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake about 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix together milk, margarine, shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat 15 minutes until fluffy.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: sauce for spaghetti
directions: First take the top off tomatoes, scald and heat.
Put through food mill.
Cook about 3 hours or until thickened.
Stir often. Add rest of the ingredients, except tomato paste.
Cook another hour or more.
Add tomato paste.
Bring to a boil.
Put in jars and seal.
Makes about 20 pints.

title: world's best creamy potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Can be topped with crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple angel food cake
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Spray Pam and flour a 9 x 13 pan.
Pour mix in pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked eggplant casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil eggplant in water until tender (approximately 15 minutes).
Drain and set aside.
Saute onions, bell peppers and parsley until clear or tender.
Add shrimp and cook approximately 10 minutes.
Add eggplant and bread crumbs; mix well.
Pour entire mixture into a 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, Mozzarella cheese, Tabasco, and Worcestershire sauce.
Bake, uncovered, approximately 25 minutes.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour and add remaining dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients to batter.
This will make a very stiff batter.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Grease 2 loaf pans with oil.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Cool for 10 minutes in pan, then place on foil and cool.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar and wrap.
This will freeze very well.

title: sloppy joe cheeseburgers
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
Saute onions and celery until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for about 20 minutes. Serve over buns.

title: rolls
directions: Rise 2 to 3 hours or overnight; punch down.
Put in muffin pan or on cookie sheet.
Cover; let rise under cover again at least 2 hours.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: block party beans
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add onion and celery and cook until tender.
Stir in soup, tomato paste and catsup.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Spoon into large kettle or roaster.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour. Feeds 25.

title: party salmon loaf
directions: Mix and shape as desired.
Chill.
Serve with Wheat Thins or Triscuits.

title: ginger cucumber pickles
directions: Peel and remove seeds from ripe cucumbers.
Cut in small pieces (5 pounds prepared).
Soak 24 hours in 2 gallons water and small box of alum.
Wash well.
Soak 6 hours in 2 gallons of water and 1 box ginger.
Soak 3 to 4 hours in 3 pints vinegar, 2 pints water, 5 pounds sugar and 1/2 box pickling spices.
Boil for 1 hour or until crystal clear (transparent).
Place in sterilized jars.
Cucumbers can soak in vinegar and sugar overnight.

title: hot cocoa
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Add water to make a paste.
Slowly add milk.
Heat but do not boil.

title: apple pie filling(to can)
directions: Fill 7 quart jars with sliced apples, packed tightly.
Boil the remaining ingredients until thick and bubbly.
Cover the apples with the syrup.
Adjust lids and process 20 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Cook noodles per package directions.
Mix meat, noodles, pizza sauce, tomato paste and soup.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 the cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Stir melted cheese into casserole.
Top with the rest of the cheese and bake another 10 minutes.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Cut Twinkies in half lengthwise.
Lay cut side up in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour pudding over this.
Spoon crushed pineapple over pudding.
Add sliced bananas.
Cover and seal edges with Cool Whip, sprinkle with nuts if desired.

title: chicken club salad
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Add enough Miracle Whip to moisten.
Add bacon.
When ready to serve, add croutons.
Serves 10.

title: rice pilaf(good with beef)
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter over medium-low heat and add onion.
Cook together until onion is tender.

title: pineapple angel dessert
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve 1 cup syrup.
Dissolve jello and marshmallows in boiling water.
Add reserved syrup.
Chill until almost thickened and then whip.
Fold in pineapple, whipped cream and cake cubes.
Pour into 10-inch cake pan or 3-quart mold and chill until firm.
Unmold and serve.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix yeast, 1 teaspoon sugar and warm water.
Set aside.
Mix together margarine and boiling water.
Stir until margarine is melted.
Add remaining sugar.
Pour into yeast mixture.
Add eggs and salt and beat well.
Put in 3 cups flour and beat until smooth with eggbeater.
Add 3 more cups of flour.
Stir well.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out, cut and put on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise 2 hours or more.
Bake at 425°.
Dough may be kept in refrigerator several days and pinched off and used as needed.

title: caramel cake
directions: Make cake according to the directions on the box.
Make 3 round layers.
Combine melted butter, milk and brown sugar. Bring to a full boil and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.	Remove from heat and
stir
in baking powder and vanilla. Stir icing until cool and
is	of spreading consistency.
(Can cool quicker if you set pan
in	cold
water
while you stir.) Spread on layers.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple and put into 9 x 13 dish.
Mix sugar, flour and cheese.
Spread over pineapple.
Melt butter.
Crumble crackers and mix with butter.
Pour over pineapple.
Bake 350° for 25 minutes.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Boil whole sweet potatoes in water until tender.
Cool, peel and slice.
Peel, core and slice apples.

title: cheesy sausage skillet
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, cook sausage and onion until sausage is brown and onion is tender, stirring often. Drain. Add potato slices, contents of sauce packet from potatoes, pepper, water, milk and margarine. Mix well. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in vegetables; simmer another 7 to 10 minutes or until potatoes and vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally. Serves 6. Prep time: 35 minutes.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
If desired, when cake is done sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix as usual.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet or make 3 rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper, then foil and freeze.
Thaw without foil in microwave 30 seconds.
Slice and bake on ungreased sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake as directed on box, using a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cake is done, remove from oven and use a wooden spoon to punch holes in cake.
Pour sweetened condensed milk and ice cream topping over cake.
Cool completely.
Top with Cool Whip and nut topping.
Keep refrigerated until time to serve.

title: texas chili
directions: *This is medium hot chili.
Reduce jalapeno pepper and Tabasco sauce for milder sauce.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix butter, sugar and beaten eggs.
Sift flour and soda.
Mash bananas.
Mix all ingredients together and pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Prepare basic biscuits; roll dough into a rectangle about 1/4-inch thick. Brush with melted butter. Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle evenly over dough. Roll up. Slice 1/2-inch thick. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Mix barbecue sauce and salad dressing.
Marinate for 1 hour. Broil or grill (low coals) for 15 minutes each side.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in an airtight container.
To serve, add 2 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup of hot water.

title: fried corn
directions: Use enough peanut oil to cover bottom of frypan.
Toss in corn, onion and pepper; stir-fry until translucent.
Add maple sugar, salt and pepper; stir and mix.
Serves 4.

title: perfection rolls
directions: Combine boiling water, sugar, and margarine. Mix until margarine is melted. Add cold water. Dissolve yeast in 1/4 c. lukewarm water. Add eggs. Add all ingredients together along with salt. Do not knead, just mix well. Cover and refrigerate until ready to use. Make out into rolls and let rise 30-45 minutes. Bake at 400°.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as package directs. Pour batter into well-greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
In a small mixer bowl, beat the cream cheese, butter and cornstarch until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then egg and vanilla until smooth.
Pour evenly over cake batter.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes, or until wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool thoroughly.

title: ginger krinkle cookies
directions: All of these ingredients can be put in a mixer bowl and mixed together well.
Make balls of dough the size of small walnuts; roll in white sugar.
Put on cookie sheet.
Space balls evenly apart; do not press down.
Bake at 350° approximately 13 minutes.
When done, they will have a crinkly top and are firm to touch.
Makes about thirty cookies (best to double the recipe).

title: apple bread
directions: Mix together.
Put in greased bread pan, then spread topping on top of bread batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy cheesy fish fillets
directions: Spray cookie sheet with Pam and set aside.
Wash fish fillets; pat dry.
Combine cheese, bread crumbs, pepper, dill weed and melted margarine.
Spread each fillet with yogurt.
Coat well with bread crumb mixture and arrange touching on prepared pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: toffee sticks
directions: Blend together butter, brown sugar, egg yolk, vanilla and salt.
Stir in flour; put in pan and bake 20 minutes at 350° until browned.
Cool.
Combine shortening, brown sugar, corn syrup, water and salt in saucepan.
Heat and stir until smooth.
Spread on top of baked dough.
Sprinkle on almonds.
Let set and cut into sticks 2 x 1-inch.

title: marshmallow cream icing
directions: Beat butter in medium bowl with mixer until creamy. Beat in marshmallow cream. When well blended, beat in powdered sugar and vanilla. Beat 3 to 4 minutes on high speed until fluffy.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Beat egg and sugar until light; add vanilla, shortening and melted chocolate; blend well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk; add nuts.
Drop small portions 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.
Cool.
Then frost with Mocha Chocolate Frosting.

title: zucchini pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil into pan and place in oven to heat.
Grate zucchini and sprinkle with salt. Allow to rest. Combine cornflakes, flour, salt, pepper and baking powder. Combine eggs, onion and carrots.
Peel potatoes and grate into egg mix. Squeeze zucchini to extract the moisture and add to egg and vegetable mix. Add flour.
Mix and pour into hot oil from baking pan.
Bake 1 hour.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix ingredients well in large bowl.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 35 minutes.
Makes two 9-inch pies or one deep dish pie.
Bake for about 15 minutes longer in deep crust.

title: lynda's corn
directions: Bake at 350° for half hour with lid on and half hour with lid off.
May be made ahead and refrigerated.

title: ham-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Chop stems.
Cook mushroom stems and onion in 1 tablespoon butter until tender. Remove from heat. Stir in ham and Parmesan cheese; set aside.

title: easy pineapple salad
directions: In saucepan, heat juice from sliced pineapple; add flour and mix well.
Simmer until thickened and add sugar; mix well and cool.
Place pineapple slices on slice of lettuce; place spoonful of mixture on each slice and top with grated cheese.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Put berries in colander; scald and drain.
Put in heavy aluminum kettle and add Epsom salts and lemon juice.
Pour sugar over berries; stir and put in a warm place until sugar dissolves. Let stand overnight.

title: chicken divan
directions: Butter dish.
Spread with broccoli.
Layer chicken.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, juice and powder.
Pour over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Next layer with fresh bread torn in pieces.
Push into cheese and sauce.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Butter should not be too soft. Add flour,
salt
and baking powder; work in with hands.
Pat into greased round 8 or 9-inch tin.
Pinch edges and prick all over with toothpick.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: hamburger and noodle dinner
directions: Fry hamburger with onion.
Cook noodles in salt water, about 8 minutes.
Put the hamburger in the casserole.
Put noodles on top. Pour tomato juice over it, then put a Velveeta cheese layer on top and bake 20 minutes.

title: chicken breast baked in juice
directions: To microwave, place ingredients in square dish (4) or rectangular dish (6).
Cover with plastic wrap venting corner. Set on Bake for 18 minutes (1000 watt), 20 minutes (750 watt), or bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple square cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and fold in at high speed.
Sift flour.
Add 1 cup at a time and beat 1 minute.
Add cream and juice, then flavorings.
Beat well.
Bake in a square pan for 40 to 60 minutes at 300°.
Cool.

title: fast 'n easy broccoli and cauliflower with cheese sauce
directions: Clean and cut up broccoli and cauliflower.
Boil, drain and put in casserole dish.
Slice your cheese and lay on top.
Put in microwave until cheese has melted and mix well.

title: italian garden soup(version 1)
directions: Combine all in large pot.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat & simmer 3 minutes.
Season to taste with salt & pepper.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix sour cream, sugar, salt and lemon juice and then add fruit and blend.
Also add nuts.
Freeze in baking cupcake papers which have been placed in medium size muffin pans.
Keep in freezer overnight, then pull baking paper cups off of frozen salad and store in Ziploc bags until ready to serve.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Cover bottom and sides of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish with tortillas.
Mix vegeburger, beans and tomato sauce together. Spread vegeburger mixture over tortillas.
Place another layer of tortillas over vegeburger mixture.
Mix up cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese and egg.
Spread over tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle rows of cheese, tomato, lettuce, green onions and olives diagonally across the center of casserole.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine in bowl the oil, zucchini, vanilla, eggs and sugar. Add salt, soda, flour, cinnamon and baking powder.
Mix together. Add nuts if desired.
Put in 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except oil) and drop from tablespoon into hot cooking oil.
Fry until light brown, drain. Makes 8 patties.

title: sarah katherine's favorite beef supreme casserole
directions: Mix, top with cheese and cook until bubbly at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cucumbers and onions with yogurt dressing
directions: Note:
May be used as a dressing if cucumbers left out.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients thoroughly; add remaining ingredients and mix.
Garnish with leftover mandarin oranges and cherry halves.
Chill about 6 hours before serving.

title: skillet potato salad
directions: In 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook bacon until browned.
Drain off all but 1/4 cup drippings.
Add onion and celery to bacon drippings.
Cook until tender over medium-high heat.

title: grandma's dessert
directions: Line bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan with graham cracker crumbs. Mix eggs, sugar, Crisco and vanilla together and spread on crumbs. Top with pineapple and then more cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with mixer and beat well.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Dough will be stiff; spread with hand.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: Mix all of these ingredients well and add to noodles.

title: colorado dip
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain.
Stir in tomatoes and chilies. Simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in cream cheese and sour cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot with nacho chips or king size Fritos.

title: ham salad
directions: Grind meat and cheese; add eggs and pickles.
Add mayonnaise. This is a real good sandwich spread.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Blend cream cheese and margarine until smooth. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Separate crescent rolls and spoon 1/4 cup chicken mixture on each triangle. Roll into crescent shape. Mix soup and milk. Pour 1/4 of mixture into baking dish. Lay crescent rolls filled with chicken on top. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and add remaining soup mixture (do not cover). Continue baking 20 minutes or until done.

title: apple spice custard cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as package directs; stir in apples.
Pour into well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.

title: carrot soup
directions: Saute bacon, onion and garlic until bacon is crisp.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling, then reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, about 20 minutes.
Cool slightly, then pour mixture in blender; process until smooth.
Garnish with a dollop of sour cream.

title: snappy bean salad
directions: Cook lima beans in small amount of water or steam them; cool. Drain
and	rinse
kidney
and
yellow
beans.
Mix all beans, onions and green pepper in bowl.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, pat out in pan.
Top with catsup and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato soup
directions: Prepare vegetables.
Place in boiler.
Add water, bouillon cubes, accent, salt and pepper and celery salt.
Cook until potatoes are tender (about 10 minutes).
Melt margarine in skillet and add flour to make a paste then gradually add milk, stirring constantly until a smooth thin sauce forms.
Pour into vegetables. Lower heat.
Allow to cook slowly to desired thickness. To speed thickening add a few instant potatoes and stir well.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and whipped topping together. Add any flavor of Jell-O powder (you can use sugar-free). Mix together.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all together.
Store in air tight can.

title: mom's brownies
directions: Melt shortening and cocoa over hot water; cool.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs until light; add sugar, then chocolate mixture.
Blend.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts; mix well.
Pour batter in 8-inch square pan (greased and floured). Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares and serve.

title: apple and peach crisp
directions: Place apples in deep pie dish.	Place peach slices with apple; spread
out
evenly
over bottom of pie dish.
Put dry cake
mix over
this.
Slice	cold
butter or oleo over other ingredients. Sprinkle
nuts
over
all of this.	Bake in 350° oven until lightly brown, 35 or 40 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes.
Cool, peel and cut up into cubes.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for several hours.

title: banana bars
directions: Cream together all ingredients.
Mix well.
Grease and flour 17 x 11-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: raisin pie
directions: Make 2 crusts; put one crust in the pan and put in filling and cover with other crust. Punch 3-4 wholes into top crust with fork, dot top crust with butter dots the size of a pea, sprinkle lightly with sugar and bake 30-35 min at 400°.

title: potato chip chicken
directions: Crush chips with rolling pin before opening chips.
Mix chips with garlic
salt
and pepper on wax paper.
Dip chicken in melted butter;
roll
in	chip
crumbs.
Place
pieces
in baking pan and pour remaining butter and crumbs over chicken. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: cousin judy's chow mein
directions: Mix all together in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat eggs lightly.
Add sugar, oil, zucchini, pineapple and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients. Mix well. Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.

title: sunflower seed roast
directions: Mix well and let store with cover over it for 1/2 hour.
Bake for 1 hour at 300° to 350°.
Serve Sunflower Seed Roast with mushroom gravy.

title: italian steak salad
directions: Cut any fat on steak at 1-inch intervals being careful not to cut into meat.
Place on unheated rack of a broiler pan.
Broil 3 inches from heat for 6 minutes.
Turn and broil to desired doneness.
Cool slightly; cut into thin slices.
Place in a nonmetallic shallow bowl.

title: blueberry oat bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine oats, flour, brown sugar and soda. Add margarine, mixing until crumbly.
Reserve 3/4 cup mixture; press remaining into 9 x 9-inch baking pan and bake 10 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients just before boiling.
Cut biscuits in 4 pieces.
Roll in white sugar and 1 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon mixed together.
Put biscuits in Bundt or regular tube pan.
Pour mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.
Let cool.

title: cheese-tuna surprise sandwiches
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
and	spread	on
split buns. Cover pan with foil and bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and butter; cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour to creamed mixture; alternate with milk, beating well.
Stir in flavoring.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Wash, devein and remove seeds from chilies, unless you really like them hot.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan:
4 chilies, Jack cheese, 4 chilies and Cheddar cheese.

title: corn bread
directions: Melt butter in a 375° oven for about 5 minutes in skillet. Combine corn meal, buttermilk, egg and oil to the other dry ingredients until dry ingredients are moistened.
Remove skillet from hot oven.
Pour batter into skillet.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
(Do not cook macaroni.)
Place in 2-quart, covered casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncover and bake another 30 minutes.

title: calico casserole
directions: Cook mixed vegetables without salt using package directions; drain.
Add celery, onion, cheese and mayonnaise; mix well.
Spoon into greased 2-quart casserole.
Mix cracker crumbs and margarine. Sprinkle over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco in large mixing bowl; add eggs one at a time, mixing after each addition.
Alternately add flour and milk, beating until creamy.
Add flavoring and nuts.
Pour mixture in greased cake pan (I use tube pan).
Bake for 1 hour and 40 minutes at 325°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 2-quart Pyrex dish.
Mix flour, baking powder, 2/3 cup sugar and milk.
Pour into pan with melted margarine.
Add 1/3 cup sugar to a large can of sliced peaches. Pour on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 45 minutes.

title: almond bark treats
directions: *Use as many as you like, usually 1 or 2 cups.

title: campfire stew
directions: In a large kettle or saucepan, cook ground beef and onion over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain, if necessary.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover; simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.

title: bubble stuff
directions: Fill jug to nearly full; add Dawn.
Add a few drops of glycerin and Voila!, bubble stuff.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Place lettuce in bottom of bowl, the pour chopped onions on top of lettuce.
Next, place peas on top of onions.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar together and spread over peas.
Placed shredded cheese on top of mayonnaise mixture.
Next, place sliced eggs; then cover with bacon bits.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Cook peas as directed on package; drain.
Shake Italian dressing, sugar and crushed red pepper in tightly covered container until blended.
Combine cooked peas, celery, green pepper, pimiento, green onions and parsley.
Gently toss pea mixture and salad dressing; season with salt and pepper.
Chill. Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Boil potatoes until soft.
Mash or whip them thoroughly and mix with all other ingredients.
Put into a buttered baking dish and bake at 300° until firm.
Brown the top under the broiler.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine and mix thoroughly.
Pour batter into pan and spread evenly.
Spread melted shortening evenly over batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: brown sugar pecans
directions: Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form. Gradually add sugar, beating until well blended.
Fold remaining ingredients into meringue.
Drop by rounded teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 30 minutes at 250°.

title: rosemary's sinfully rich coconut cream pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and egg yolks.
Add 1 cup milk and stir until all lumps are gone.
Add rest of milk and cook over low heat,
stirring
constantly
so mixture will not stick to bottom of	pan.
Cook
until
slightly
thickened,
then
add coconut. Add
flavorings
and
coloring.
Cook about 1 minute longer, stirring
constantly.
Pour
mixture into pie crusts. Top
with whipping cream.
Sprinkle a little coconut over top to garnish.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix and bake cornbread.
Cool and crumble.
Cook sausage and drain well.
Chop onion, pepper, pickles and tomato.
Ad mayonnaise and juice.
Stir in sausage and all but 1/2 cup bread. Use on top with green pepper garnish.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into thick slices.
Add water and boil until tender.
Drain and reserve 1 cup of the liquid.
Return cup of liquid to stove and combine with next five ingredients.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove and stir in peanut butter.
Line a baking dish with the sweet potatoes and pour sauce over.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Bake in uncooked pie shell for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach pasta salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the macaroni, artichoke hearts, olives, roasted pepper, onion and cheeses.
Toss to mix.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and boil (fast boil) one minute. Remove from heat.
Add last 3 ingredients and drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.

title: sweet potato croquettes
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, celery and salt; mix well and stir in milk.
Shape into 6 balls.
Dip in melted butter and roll each in corn flakes.
Place croquettes on a broiler pan.
Broil 6 to 7 inches from heat for 5 minutes, turning until golden brown on all sides.

title: turnip green casserole
directions: Cook greens and turnips separately.
Salt to taste.
Drain both.
In 2 quart casserole place greens then turnips.
Chop onion and place on top.
Crumble cornbread on top.
Melt margarine and pour over cornbread.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: creamy dream pie
directions: Whip together the whipping cream, vanilla and sugar until it peaks.
Add the condensed milk and mix well by hand.
Add lemon juice and almond extract, again stirring well by hand.
Pour into graham cracker crust and top with cherry pie filling.
Chill and serve.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Break potatoes into bite size pieces. Sprinkle with seasoning salt.
Gently heat butter and cheese; add half and half.
Heat until smooth.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake uncovered for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: healthy salad
directions: This salad is very good for your health.

title: jo ann's pound cake
directions: Mix the cream cheese and margarine together.
Mix the flour, sugar and salt together.
Add the eggs, beating well after each, and vanilla
Combine the flour mixture with the cream cheese mixture.
Beat well.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: roly-poly carrot marbles
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cheddar cheese and honey.
Mix in carrots and chill for 1 hour.
Shape in balls, using 1 1/2 teaspoons for each ball.
Roll in chopped nuts and chill until firm.

title: sausage cheese puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop marble size balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Will be light golden when done.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix the three ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured cake pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes only.
Frost with a chocolate fudge frosting mix.

title: barbecued alligator
directions: Sprinkle alligator with vinegar and then roll in the mustard, salt and pepper.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Barbecue on low fire without basting for about 1 hour.
Butterfly fillet by slicing in half and placing the outside down.
Baste inside with your favorite barbecue sauce and cook until done.

title: effortless five-hour stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in large casserole.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours.
No stirring.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Melt together milk and caramels in top of double boiler.
Stir in pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls onto Pam sprayed cookie sheet. (Place in freezer for at least 40 minutes for easier dipping.)
In double boiler, melt paraffin and chocolate chips.
Dip clusters in chocolate.

title: sausage balls(club member: brigitte magee)
directions: Mix all with fingers and roll into small balls. Put about 1 inch apart. Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Soak together for 1 hour the eggs, raisins and vanilla.
Cream the shortening and sugars.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add to other mixtures.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Sift together the first 4 ingredients.
Add the shortening, buttermilk and mashed banana.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Fold in the chopped nuts.
Pour batter into prepared pans (2 round 9-inch layers).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Fill layer and frost with your favorite frosting.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: three layer dessert
directions: Crust:
Melt oleo.
Mix with flour and salt.
Cool and spread in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: First, pop 6 quarts of popcorn.
Cook in order given for 5 minutes (brown sugar, oleo, salt, syrup and cream of tartar).
Add 1/2 teaspoon of soda; stir and pour over popcorn.
Mix.
Put on 2 greased (oleo) cookie sheets and bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat and drain; add chili powder, cumin, salt and pepper. Melt cheese over very low heat; stir in Ro-Tel tomatoes (undrained). Layer lettuce, fresh tomatoes, onion, green pepper, crumbled Fritos, hot meat and melted cheese on top. Serves 5 to 6.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Mix rice, consomme and water in with butter.
Mix in onions and mushrooms, if desired.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat well-greased 8 or 10-inch heavy skillet in 425° oven, using 1 tablespoon lard about 10 minutes.
Blend all ingredients and pour into skillet or pan.
Bake in 425° oven for 25 to 30 minutes for 8-inch skillet; 20 to 25 minutes for 10-inch skillet.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Combine butter, sugar and water. Boil, stirring constantly, to soft ball stage, 236°. Add vanilla. Serve hot or cold with ice cream.

title: batter recipe
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Set aside.
Put one egg in cup; beat well.
Add enough milk to fill cup.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Stir well.
Use as batter for deep frying vegetables or fish.

title: coffee can bread(hobo bread)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Then add 2 tablespoons sugar, oil, evaporated milk and salt.
Add flour 1 cup at a time.
Beat thoroughly.
Last cup will have to be beaten by hand.
Put into well-greased 1-pound coffee cans.
Place lids on.
Let rise until lids pop.
Then bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Then let stand 5 to 10 minutes and remove from cans.

title: coffee cake
directions: Warm together shortening, sugar, milk and yeast.
(Check yeast first.)
Add salt and flour and knead dough.
Let set 1 1/2 hours (about double).
Knock down and let rise again to double.
Roll dough to approximately
12 x 18-inches (jelly roll).
Brush butter and add sugar and cinnamon.
(Roll up as for jelly roll.)
Can also add sliced apples and nuts.
Cut about 1-inch thick and put in pan.
Butter tops of dough and let rise again to double.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 to 25 minutes, until very brown.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Cut in margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Add egg whites, orange peel and orange juice all at once.
Stir just until mixture is evenly moist.
Fold in cranberries.
Spoon evenly into two greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Cream sugar and butter; beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately to batter.
Stir in berries.
Spread batter in lightly greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle with streusel topping. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.

title: guatemalan  rice(arroz guatemalteco)
directions: Heat oil in saucepan and add rice.
Saut lightly until rice has absorbed the oil, be careful not to let it brown.
Add mixed vegetables, salt, pepper and chicken broth.
Bring to a boil, cover, and reduce heat to low.
Cook for 20 minutes or until rice is done and liquid is absorbed.
Serves 6-8.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken
and save the broth. Cut chicken from bones and into bite size pieces.
Put in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix chicken soup with 2 cups of chicken broth until creamy.
Pour half over chicken in dish and put dressing on top of this and add remaining soup mix on top of dressing.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: chicken divan
directions: In 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange broccoli and chicken. Combine soup and milk; pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese over soup mixture.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbling.
Serves 4.

title: cheese ring
directions: Mix all ingredients, except strawberry preserves.
Pack in ring mold sprayed with vegetable spray and chill.
Unmold on platter and place strawberry preserves in center.
Line edge of platter with buttery crackers.
Serves lots.

title: brown rice
directions: Put the first four ingredients in baking pan.
Pour in rice. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican pizzas
directions: If you itemize the terms of cooks,

title: spam 'n spuds
directions: Slice Spam into 8 slices.
Slice potatoes.
Place Spam and potatoes on 4 squares of foil.
Top with maple syrup, one tablespoon on each packet.
Close tightly and heat on grill.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat bacon drippings or oil over medium heat in large skillet. Add rice, stirring constantly, until rice is browned.
Be careful not to burn rice.
Turn burner off.
Add tomato sauce, water and salts or garlic and onion.
Cover immediately.
Simmer over low heat until all liquid is evaporated and rice, onion and garlic are tender, 25 to 30 minutes.
Add more water if necessary to prevent drying.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: chicken scampi
directions: Heat olive oil in large fry pan or wok over medium-high heat. Add chicken and stir-fry about 5 minutes.
Remove chicken and reserve.
Add broccoli and stir-fry 4 minutes.
Add onion and green pepper; stir-fry 5 more minutes.
Add chicken to pan and stir-fry 5 minutes more.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Boil linguine in large pot of boiling water; drain.
Place pasta in large serving dish; top with chicken-vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: raspberry rice cream
directions: Cook rice until tender; add sugar, salt and butter.
Let cool. When rice is cool, whip cream and fold into rice.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Serve with Raspberry Sauce.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Put 1 cup (minus 2 tablespoons) sugar in heavy skillet with butter and cream.
On medium heat, brown to a dark golden syrup. Stir and watch closely.
Combine flour, 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/4 cup milk and mix well.
Add egg yolks, salt, vanilla and remaining milk.
Pour into syrup and cook slowly until smooth.
If not thick enough, a little more flour mixed with small quantity of milk to make paste may be added now.
Cook, then pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and bake about 400° for 10 minutes.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Combine mayonnaise, cream of mushroom soup and cream cheese over low heat until melted.
Stir in gelatin, then onion, celery and shrimp.
Chill in mold until set.
Unmold on plate.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Melt butter. Add other ingredients and beat.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain.
Mix together in large bowl and add in this order:
Mayonnaise, salt, pepper, celery and salad cubes.
Stir until well blended together.

title: sugarless health cookies (diabetic)
directions: Cook raisins and dates in water; boil for 3 minutes.
Add vegetable shortening; cool in refrigerator.
Beat eggs, Sugar Twin and vanilla.
Mix with dates and raisins.
Add flour and baking soda.
Mix well.
Refrigerate mixture at least 1 hour.

title: country-style barbecued spareribs
directions: Saute onion in butter until golden brown; stir in next 10 ingredients.
Bring sauce to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Place ribs, meaty side up, on a rack in a shallow baking dish.
Bake at 325° for about 2 hours or until well done, basting with sauce and turning every 30 minutes.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Form into cylinder-like cones or balls.
Blend 1 egg and 1 tablespoon water.
Roll croquettes in fine cracker crumbs, then in egg mixture and again in cracker crumbs (or cracker meal). Fry in deep fryer at 390° or in deep fat in skillet until golden brown all over.
Drain well.
In place of salmon, 2 cups cooked, chopped ham, chicken or beef without bones or skin may be used.

title: hot sherry crab dip(a winner every time!)
directions: In double boiler, melt cheese until soft.
Add remaining ingredients except crab and stir until smooth.
Fold in crab. Serve hot in chafing dish with bagel chips.
Can make ahead and reheat at 350° until hot.
Serves 20.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except corn flakes.
Pour into a buttered glass dish, 9 x 13-inch, then sprinkle corn flakes on top. Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 people.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix onion, carrot, celery, chicken, salad dressing and mayonnaise together.
Then add shoestring potato sticks.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add mashed bananas.
Add soda, salt and baking powder to flour and sift together.
Add to other ingredients.
Last, add chopped nuts. Bake in 3 loaf pans at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
(This bread freezes well.)

title: poppy seed pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer until smooth.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes in a Bundt pan at 350°.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place Tater Tots, butter and onion in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup, sour cream and cheese.
Pour over Tater Tots.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Add crushed French fried onions during the last 5 minutes of baking.

title: baked ocean perch
directions: Set oven to 400°.
Cover bottom of baking dish with lemon and onion slices.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Lay fillets on top.
Cover.
(If pan does not have cover, use foil.)
Bake for 20 minutes.
Remove cover.
Combine remaining ingredients; spread over top.
Broil 3 minutes below heat, until brown.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix together. Boil on low heat until it thickens.
Pour over biscuits with butter.

title: microwave rice 'n honey chops
directions: In
quart
x
8-inch) baking dish, combine rice, orange juice,
raisins and salt.
Stir to mix.
Arrange chops on
top, pressing into rice mixture.
Drizzle honey over top. Cook, covered
with
wax paper, 16 minutes or until chops are done.
If desired, remove paper the last two minutes and spoon some
rice over
chops.
Or
after
cooking,
place pan under broiler a few minutes to brown chops. Serves four.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream in butter with sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla and vinegar; preheat oven to 425°.
Cook for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 300°; bake for 30 to 40 minutes (total time, 40 to 50 minutes).

title: peach pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and margarine.
Add Cool Whip and peaches. Blend until well mixed.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
In a large dish, put a layer of wafers and a layer of peach mixture until all is used.
Put in refrigerator and chill for several hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade, still frozen, with condensed milk and stir well. Fold in Cool Whip and pour into graham cracker crust. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in salt water as directed on box.
Chop pepper, onion and pickles fine.
Toss with macaroni after draining and cooled.
Add salad dressing.
Sprinkle sugar and toss again.

title: potato puff
directions: Combine the mashed potatoes, beaten egg yolks, cream and butter.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Heap lightly into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish and bake in a 350° oven until puffed and brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer in glass bowl in order given. Refrigerate overnight.

title: strudel
directions: Roll dough out and spread apricot preserves, walnuts, white raisins, sugar and cinnamon. Roll like a jellyroll and brush melted butter over top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sour cream cashew drops
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Blend dry ingredients (flour, baking powder, soda and salt) together.
Put egg, butter, brown sugar, vanilla and sour cream and mix on low. Add nuts.
Try not to overmix nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheets.
Bake about 10 minutes. Cool and frost with Creamy White Frosting.
Makes about 7 dozen cookies.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of double boiler, stirring constantly until mixture is blended and well heated.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: old fashioned raisin pie
directions: Combine raisins and water; boil for 5 minutes.
Blend sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and and salt.
Add to raisins and cook, stirring until clear.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vinegar and butter.
Cool slightly.
Pour into pie crust.
Cover with second pie crust.
Bake at 425° for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: peach delight
directions: Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: pot pie no. 2
directions: Wash meat.
Heat fat and onion in pan in which pot pie is to be baked.
Add the meat, sprinkle the flour over meat and brown meat, stirring occasionally until uniformly browned.

title: coconut mist cake
directions: Cream oleo and add sugar and water.
Cream until fluffy.
Beat egg yolks.
Add the combined flour, baking powder and salt alternately with the milk, a small amount at a time.
Stir in vanilla and coconut, then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into three 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350°.
Prepare pie filling according to package directions and spread between layers.
Cover with Seven Minute Icing.

title: spicy chili sauce
directions: Bring to boil, simmer until thick 1 to 2 hours.
Stir frequently, pour boiling into jar 1/8-inch headspace.
Makes 8 pints.

title: baba ghanouj
directions: Pierce the eggplant and either broil in a barbecue or bake in the oven until wrinkled and soft.
Place under cold running water and peel.
Mash in a bowl.
Pound the garlic with salt, then add tahina, lemon juice and water.
Add this mixture to the mashed eggplant and mix well.
Spread on a platter and decorate with parsley leaves.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken with artichokes
directions: Cut chicken breasts into strips.
Dip strips in flour.
Shake excess.
Saute in butter.
Add wine.
Cut up artichoke hearts. Toss with chicken.
Season to taste with basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook until done, about 20 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Add seasonings and tomato sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Slice zucchini lengthwise into 1/4-inch slices and arrange the slices in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Beat cottage cheese and egg together and spread on the zucchini.
Top with half the sauce and cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until tender.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: antonie novak's potato soup
directions: Peel
and
cut potatoes into bite-size pieces.
Put the potatoes,
salt
and
caraway seed in water and cook.
Mix the flour
and cream together.
When potatoes are almost done, add the milk
and pepper.
Bring it to a boil; add cream mixture. Stir and
continue cooking for five more minutes on low heat. While this
is cooking, beat the egg and with a fork, dribble little drips into potato mixture and stir.
If too thick, add a little milk.
Onion may be added when cooking potatoes.

title: mama's chicken getti
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Brown onion and celery.
Add onion, celery, cut up pimentos, chicken soup, broth, salt and pepper in a casserole with spaghetti (already cooked).
Stir.
Cover and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and boil 30 minutes on medium heat.
Seal while hot.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except corn flakes, and put in a greased casserole pan.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: tomato-cheese strata
directions: In skillet, heat butter, green pepper, onion, sugar, salt, pepper and oregano for about 10 minutes.
Toast bread at 400° until lightly browned.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place bread in dish, spoon half of mixture over bread.
Arrange overlapping rows of tomato and cheese over mixture.
Spoon remaining mixture on top.
Cover dish with foil and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Uncover and bake 6 minutes longer.

title: perfect pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; add alternatively whipping cream and flour.
Add vanilla.
Place cake in tube pan and put in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not open oven doors to peek!

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Cook sugar, eggs, flour and milk until thick.
Add in coconut. Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with beaten egg whites.
Sprinkle with coconut and brown.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until light.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Add flavoring.
Mix flour in lightly.
Bake in angel food pan or two loaf pans.
Put in cold oven.
Turn to 325°.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done (makes it crusty).

title: hot crab spread
directions: Blend all ingredients and bake for 15 minutes in a 350° oven. Serve with crackers or party rye.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter; add beef bouillon, French onion soup, 1/2 cup water and rice.
Lay pork chops or chicken over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no fail chocolate or sour cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well with mixer.

title: saucy cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, egg and salt and shape into small meatballs. Makes about 50.
(I make larger meatballs.) Roll them in a little flour and fry in pan until brown.
(They can also be broiled instead in a shallow pan.)

title: shrimp scampi with rice
directions: Saute shrimp, garlic and onion in butter and oil over medium heat until shrimp are pink (3 to 4 minutes).
Add broth, zucchini, lemon juice and salt.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice and parsley.
Cover, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork.

title: sunburst(drink)
directions: Combine ingredients in blender. Run on high until smooth and well blended.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 cups.

title: rhubarb strawberry dessert
