directions: Wash and cut rhubarb.
Put in greased 9 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with the rest of the ingredients in order given.
Drizzle butter on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Good served with ice cream.

title: chocolate-almond zucchini bread
directions: Into large bowl, sift together first 6 ingredients.
Stir in almonds; set aside.
In medium bowl, mix oil, vanilla and eggs until well blended.
Stir in melted chocolate until well blended. Stir in zucchini.
Stir zucchini mixture into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove; cool on rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Mix eggs, mayonnaise, grated cheese and cream of mushroom soup.
Mix in broccoli and pour into 1 or 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over it and bake at 350° until brown, approximately 30 minutes,

title: cheddar cheese ball
directions: Let cheese warm to room temperature.
Roll all ingredients into a ball.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Roll in pecans.
Makes large cheese ball.
Can divide into two.

title: low-fat meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/4 cup catsup.
Press into loaf pan and spread 1/4 cup catsup over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Allow to sit a few minutes before slicing. Serves 8.

title: how to make your own powdered sugar
directions: Do one cup at a time in the blender on high for 2 minutes.

title: chopped liver the way benjamin's grandpop joe used to make it
directions: Exact quantities are not critical, but an overall flavor balance is the goal.
Suggested quantities might be:
2 pounds each beef and chicken livers, 4 or 5 sliced onions (they really cook down), 4 hard-boiled eggs, 1/8 box of saltines and the fat from two fryer-sized chickens.

title: hard tack candy
directions: Combine sugar, Karo and water in large pan.
Heat to 310°, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add flavoring and coloring immediately.
Pour into buttered cookie sheet; let cool, then crack into small pieces.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend in blender until smooth.
Serve with bite-sized pieces of fresh vegetables.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and drain mushrooms; remove stems.
Mix together and put a dab in each mushroom cap.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 400° until they start to brown.

title: peppered beef with asparagus
directions: Rub half the pepper over the steak.
Turn and rub remaining pepper on the other side.
Broil 10 to 15 minutes or until done. Cook asparagus.

title: chocolate pudding cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: rayma's salad
directions: Toss pasta with olive oil and lemon juice; cool to room temperature.
Add basil, tomatoes, cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Serve same day at room temperature.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Press firmly into greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch pan (loaf).
Bake about 1 hour.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before slicing.
Put catsup on top.

title: carob chip cookies
directions: Place cashews and water into blender and blend until smooth. Add dates, vanilla, sea salt and rice (with the exception of flour) and continue blending until smooth.
Pour into a mixing bowl and add flour and the other ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoon onto sprayed cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rhubarb-strawberry jam(easy)
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar; cover all day or overnight.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add jello; stir.
Cool slightly.
Pour into jars.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press basic dough into a buttered pizza pan.
If using Pillsbury dough, slice in 1/8-inch slices and place in pan and bake according to package directions.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: In a large saucepan, saute the tomatoes, mushrooms, red pepper, yellow squash, zucchini, carrot, onion, and garlic on oil until crisp-tender. Stir in the tomato paste, broth, brown sugar, and seasonings. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix the thawed and drained spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise and vegetable soup mix until well blended.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: summer squash salad
directions: Toss squashes and radishes in bowl. Combine remaining ingredients. Mix well and pour over vegetables. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Makes 12-16 servings.

title: cherry dessert torte
directions: Mix well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Cool. Crumble well and pat firmly back in pan.

title: zucchini bisque
directions: In a 2 to 3-quart saucepan, saute onion in heated butter until golden brown.
Add zucchini, chicken broth, nutmeg, basil, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes or until zucchini is cooked.
Turn half of mixture into blender bowl or food processor. Process until pureed.
Repeat with remaining half of mixture. Return mixture to pan.
Stir in half and half.
Heat to steaming. Correct seasoning.
Top each serving with a lemon slice and sliced green onion, if desired.

title: passover spinach souffle
directions: Cook and stir onion and garlic in butter until tender.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter, flour, oats, cinnamon and nutmeg together until crumbly.
Slice apples thin (like you would for a pie).
Sprinkle with some sugar and cinnamon; place in baking dish and cover apples with the crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 minutes, until crumbs are brownish.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well. Cover mixture and refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Serve with slotted spoon.

title: chicken noodle soup(yield: 40 servings)
directions: 1. Split chicken in half.
Put 8 cups of water and chicken broth in a 5-quart pot.
Add chicken and onion.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and cook for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lo-fat flounder continental(heart healthy)
directions: Baking Temperature: 325°.
Baking Time: 25 minutes.

title: crumbled apple pie topping
directions: Combine flour and sugar. Cut in butter, using fork. Mix until butter is crumbly. Cover apples. Bake
Enjoy!

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into container.
Use 1/3 cup of mixture for each cup of hot water.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown and drain hamburger. Add jar of salsa and velveeta cheese. Combine into crock pot and melt cheese. So good on nacho chips.

title: lime jello fluff
directions: Drain pears.
Add enough water to juice to make 3 cups.
Heat to boiling. Add cream cheese.
Heat again after cream cheese is dissolved.
Stir.
Pour over Jell-O in fairly large bowl.
Stir until all is dissolved.
Add mashed pears (or blend them). Cool until slightly thickened. Fold in Cool Whip.

title: tomato pie
directions: Bake pie crust golden brown.
Peel and slice tomatoes (enough to fill pie crust).
Drain on paper towel until juice is out. Fill pie crust with tomatoes.
Cover tomatoes with thin slices of onion.
Mix mayonnaise and grated Cheddar cheese together.
(The amount of topping is up to the individual.)
Bake in a 350° oven until brown.

title: texas hash(student favorite)
directions: Fry together meat, onions and pepper.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased, covered, 2-quart casserole at 350° for one hour.

title: apple cake
directions: Soften butter.
Cut butter into dry cake mix.
Stir in coconut. Pat into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, building up a slight edge. Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Arrange well drained apple slices on warm crust.
Sprinkle with sugar cinnamon mixture. Combine sour cream and egg yolks.
Pour over apples (will not completely cover cake).
Bake for 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend about 30 seconds or until all is blended.
Delicious!

title: surprise squares
directions: Mix well with beater and pour on top of first layer.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: country hot relish
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir well.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.
Sauce may be kept in refrigerator for up to one week.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl until well blended. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift the flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt into a 10 x 7-inch dish or an 8-inch or a 9-inch square baking dish.
With an index finger, make 3 holes in the mixture.
Pour butter in one hole, vinegar in another hole and the vanilla in the third hole. Pour water over all.
With fork, stir mixture until well combined. Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until tester is clean when removed.
Immediately top cake with chocolate chips and bake 2 to 3 minutes longer, just until soft.
With rubber spatula, spread chips evenly over top of cake.
Cool to room temperature.
Serve with ice cream, if desired.

title: meatballs in mustard sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Form into 3/4 to 1-inch balls.
Brown in hot fat.
Put in crock-pot.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch cake pan or dish.
Line with crackers. Mix pudding and milk and Cool Whip in separate bowl.
Alternate crackers and the pudding mix.
Finish off pudding mix with one layer of graham crackers.
Heat chocolate frosting for a minute to soften and spread over crackers.
Refrigerate.

title: sandies
directions: Cream margarine and 1/4 cup confectioners sugar.
Add vanilla and water; mix well.
Add flour; mix well.
Add pecans.
Form small rolls or round balls (mash with thumb).
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 25 minutes at 300°, or until lightly browned. While hot, roll in confectioners sugar.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain well.
Add carrot, onion, pimiento, soup and sour cream.
Melt butter.
Add the stuffing to the butter; toss to coat.
Add 1/2 or 3/4 stuffing to the squash mixture; mix well.
Put into a 3-quart casserole that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, baking powder, baking soda, flour, salt, sour cream and flavoring.
Blend well.
Layer 1/2 batter in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Spread 1/2 cranberry sauce over batter.
Top with remaining batter and remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool.
Drizzle with 3/4 cup confectioners sugar, 2 teaspoons warm water and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Place chopped apples in pie crust.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl and pour over apples. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cabbage-apple slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, carrots, green pepper, apples and onion. Combine yogurt, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Pour yogurt mix over vegetables.
Toss until well coated.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with dry Italian dressing and spread on party ryes.
Place slice of cucumber on top and sprinkle with dill.

title: outer banks crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into serving size cakes.
Fry quickly in a little oil until brown.

title: paradise chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Arrange chicken pieces barely touching in shallow baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to boil, then simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Spoon half the sauce over chicken.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes.
Uncover; spoon on rest of sauce.
Continue baking uncovered until tender (15 to 20 minutes).
Serves 4 to 6.

title: instant reuben
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with party rye bread.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in dish.
Add Cheddar cheese on top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ham soup
directions: In a dutch oven or larger pot, put ham bones in and cover with cold water. Add celery, onions, and carrots. Bring all of this to a boil. Turn heat down to low and cook 2 - 3
hours. Add potatoes or macaroni, stewed tomatoes, peas, veg soup mix, parsley and basil. Cook for a while longer and take bones out and add meat to soup.

title: raggedy ann cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar, shortening, egg and maple flavoring until fluffy.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Stir in coconut.
Drop by spoonfuls 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Dip bottom of small glass into granulated sugar and press cookies flat (edges will be ragged).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: cheesy spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Rinse with warm water and drain.
Saute onion and green pepper; add Glutenburger and fry until brown.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Combine with spaghetti and place into casserole dish.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add all ingredients and mix together.
Put into crock-pot.
Cover top with slices of cheese. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cook 3 to 4 hours on low.

title: reese's chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Combine butter or margarine and sugar in large mixing bowl. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Gradually blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Do not overbake.
(Cookies are soft, they will puff during baking and flatten upon cooling.)
Cool about 1 minute.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Cool completely before storing.

title: french coconut pies
directions: Beat eggs well. Add milk, then sugar and flour; mix well. Add coconut and pour into shells and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients with the jello made with the hot water and sugar to suit your taste.
Can be frozen.
Use small boxes of jello. Cranberries, apples, oranges and nuts should be ground.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar; cut in butter to make crumb mixture.
Set aside.
Mix soda, spices, molasses and hot water.
Put 1/3 crumb mixture in bottom of pie crust.
Pour in liquid.
Put rest of crumb mixture on top.
Put 4 holes in crumb mixture and let some liquid come through.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then reduce to 350° for 20 minutes.
This is a "wet bottom" Shoo-Fly pie.

title: diabetic banana cake
directions: Combine eggs, jelly, and vanilla and beat for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients and beat for 1 minute.
Use Pam spray on 6 1/2 x 10 inch pyrex dish. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 25 - 30 minutes.
Serve with a dollop of heavy cream or Cool Whip.

title: dallas dippers
directions: In medium bowl, combine Bisquick, water and chili powder to form soft dough.
On a lightly floured board, knead 5 times. Divide into 16 equal parts.
Shape each into a ball
on the board. Sprinkle with corn meal.
Roll each ball into a 4-inch circle. Drop circle into hot oil in fryer.
Fry until puffy and golden. Drain and serve warm or cold.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta according to package directions.
Toss with all remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight or at least several hours.
Toss again and serve.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni until tender; drain.
In a saucepan, heat milk, butter, salt and pepper on low heat until butter has melted. Grate 3/4 of cheese in large bowl.
Pour macaroni over cheese while hot, then add sauce.
Mix together well and pour into casserole dish.
Top with remainder of cheese, grated.
Place in oven at 350° until cheese melts.

title: fruit chess pie
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, flour and eggs.
Fold in fruit and cinnamon.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 325°
and bake 40 minutes longer.

title: butter pecan bars
directions: Cream butter, sugar and salt together.
Add flour.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, until light brown.

title: crab and shrimp gumbo(or shrimp and okra gumbo)
directions: Mix oil and flour in pan; cook over low heat, stirring, until gravy is the color of dark brown but not burned.
Saute onions in 3 tablespoons butter until soft, about 5 minutes.
Stir in okra; saute until okra is tender, 3 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes; saute 30 minutes.
Saute green pepper and garlic in 2 tablespoons butter in skillet 5 minutes.
Add shrimp; saute until pink, 5 minutes.
Add shrimp mixture and all other mixtures to pot.
Cook on simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from heat for 10 minutes.
Eat over rice.

title: apple butter
directions: Bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Stir often.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in large saucepan.
Cook and stir until soft ball stage (about 15 minutes after it comes to a boil).
Then take off heat; add marshmallow cream, chocolate chips and nuts.
Stir until creamy.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Put in refrigerator until firm.
Cut when firm.

title: spicy perked punch
directions: Mix first three ingredients and pour into bottom of electric percolator.
Place remaining ingredients in basket and perk 10 minutes until spices are permeated.
Serve hot.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Cook turkey until well done.
Mince it up and add the broth it was cooked in.
Add water if not enough broth to cover meat.
Add soda crackers, which have been crushed fine.
Simmer 1/2 hour. Serves a large group.
Freezes well, too.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Layer ingredients in casserole dish.
Squeeze lemon juice over all.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 45 minutes (covered with foil).

title: soft pineapple cookies
directions: Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool and ice, if desired, with powdered sugar, Pet milk and cream cheese.
Good for freezing.

title: jonathan's favorite vegetable pancakes
directions: Grate carrot and zucchini.
Slice scallions.
Combine flour, baking powder, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Beat together egg, milk, carrot, zucchini and scallion.
Stir wet ingredients into dry, just until combined.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a frying pan over medium heat.
Pour batter by tablespoonfuls into pan, making a few pancakes at a time.
Cook until golden, about 2 minutes on each side.
Add remaining oil to pan as needed.

title: corn salad
directions: Place all vegetables in a bowl.
Pour dressing mixture and mix together.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: bacon, tomato and herb dip
directions: Mix all.
Cover and chill.
Serve with vegetables, crackers or chips.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Place cream cheese in a small bowl.
Chop or grind onions and 2 or 3 slices of beef together.
Add this to the cream cheese. Add Accent.
Mix well.
Chop or grind remainder of dried beef (fairly fine).
Place beef on an aluminum square.
Put cheese mixture on top of beef.
Form a ball by covering the cheese with the beef.
Wrap with aluminum foil and refrigerate.
Serve with Ritz or your favorite crackers.

title: holiday ham glaze
directions: Bake ham at 325° for 2 hours.
Glaze ham with above ingredients every 15 minutes for second hour.
Remove ham; let stand for 5 minutes.
Carve.

title: chewy cake
directions: Melt margarine over low heat or in microwave.
Add sugar. Stir until dissolved.
Add eggs, one at a time, until mixed well. Blend in flour and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add nuts and bake at 325° to 350° until brown (about 30 minutes).
Place in a sheet cake pan.

title: tuna or chicken oriental
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: pecan squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Press into 9 x 13 buttered pan.
Chill 20 minutes. Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Mix next 5 ingredients together for filling.
Heat until melted and boil for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients to filling mixture. Pour over first layer. Bake at 325° until bubbly, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pork chop marinade
directions: Shake meat tenderizer on pork chops sparingly.
Marinate in sauce overnight in refrigerator.
Put on grill until done.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugars.
Mix well.
Add egg and vanilla; mix.
Blend dry ingredients into mixture.
Roll in balls, then roll in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and place candy kiss on.

title: roasted and marinated green beans with onions and garlic cloves
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Brush a large baking tray with 2 tablespoons olive oil.

Spread green beans, onion and garlic on the tray. Salt lightly and drizzle with another tablespoon or two of olive oil. Bake the vegetables for 20 to 30 minutes, interrupting several times to shake the tray or stir briefly. After 20 minutes, taste-test a green bean to see if it's done to your liking. The baking time is somewhat flexible.
When all the vegetables are tender, remove from the oven and transfer to a bowl.
Drizzle immediately with vinegar. Apply freshly ground black pepper to taste.
Serve hot at room temperature or cold. Preparation time:
10 minutes to prepare, 20 to 30 to bake. Yields about 4 servings.

title: 7-up and ale punch
directions: Place frozen juices in a large pan; add 7-Up and ginger ale. Mix and serve.
Serves 30 to 50 people.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Blend cheese and milk; stir in beef, onion, green pepper and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in sour cream.
Sprinkle nuts over top. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: grandma's egg pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients and bake in an unbaked pie shell for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rum balls
directions: Crush the vanilla wafers and chop the pecans.
Mix all of the ingredients together except the confectioners sugar.
Chill the dough for 4 hours.
Shape into marble-size balls and roll in confectioners sugar.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: shrimp stuffed eggplant
directions: Parboil eggplant 15 minutes, until almost tender.
Cut each into 3 wedges.
Remove pulp and chop.
Place shells on greased baking sheet.
Pour water over bread.
Squeeze out extra moisture. Saute onion.
Add salt, garlic and celery tops; cook 2 minutes. Add chopped eggplant, bread, butter and seasoning.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix together in skillet and stir.
Cook to desired thickness. Good with toast or biscuits.
This recipe was given to me in 1938 from Annie Allen.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Stir all dry ingredients in large bowl.
Make a hole in center; add the remaining ingredients.
Mix with electric beater until creamy.
Pour into three well-greased 1 pound coffee cans about 2/3 full.
Do not flour. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
One pound loaf pans may be used.

title: spinach manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

Cook beef, onion, and garlic in skillet until brown; drain. Add tomatoes, mushrooms, parsley, salt, fennel seed, and basil in skillet; break up tomatoes, heat to boiling, then reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Mix 3 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon in small dish and set aside.
Cream 1 cup sugar and shortening; add eggs and apple.
Mix in dry ingredients to which nutmeats have been added.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into greased loaf pan; sprinkle top with mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Bake 1 hour in preheated oven at 350°.

title: english muffin pizza
directions: Spread each muffin with 1 tablespoon spaghetti sauce.
Top with topping garnish.
Arrange little pizza in a circular pattern on a microwave plate.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: chocolate chip clusters
directions: Melt chips, peanut butter and paraffin in double boiler.
Add roasted peanuts.
Beat; drop into cluster on wax paper.
Makes approximately 80 clusters.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Combine the ingredients, blending well.
Add enough flour to stiffen dough.
Wrap up batter and chill overnight.
Roll dough out to 1/4 to 1/8-inch and use gingerbread cutter.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sharon's right side up pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan. In a small saucepan, combine undrained pineapple and brown sugar over medium-high heat. Boil for 5 minutes, reducing heat if necessary. Do not let sugar mixture burn. Pour over top of baked cake and allow to cool. Prepare instant pudding as package instructions; add softened cream cheese. Blend

thoroughly. Pour over top of cooled cake. Slice bananas and place evenly on top of cake. Top with whipped topping, covering completely. Sprinkle with pecans, then coconut. Decorate with maraschino cherry halves. Refrigerate.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine over high heat until soft.
Add flour and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add chicken broth.
Add broccoli, tarragon, garlic powder, thyme and black pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until broccoli is tender.
Add milk and simmer uncovered 5 minutes.
Add 1/4 at a time to blender and blend at medium speed until smooth.
Return to saucepan and simmer until heated through.

title: 24-hour salad
directions: Layer lettuce, green pepper, celery and peas.
Mix sugar with mayonnaise and spread on top.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon on top of mayonnaise.
Cover with Saran Wrap
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Soften margarine and
cream
cheese.
Mix
with
flour. Work into a ball and roll out onto wax paper.
Spread sausage over dough
to the edges.
Roll up into a log.
(Will be long; should divide
into
logs.)
Wrap in wax paper or foil and refrigerate overnight.	Slice and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill.
Good with fresh veggies.

title: no-guilt bacon cheeseburger
directions: Fry patty in skillet with turkey bacon until both are done. Remove to paper towels; pat dry.
Assemble ingredients as for a hamburger with cheese and bacon on top of beef patty.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Stir eggs, salad oil, sugar and vanilla with a spoon until thick.
Beat in zucchini and pineapple.
Combine flour with baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add walnuts to flour mixture.
Combine zucchini and flour mixtures.
Boil currants or raisins, then drain.
Stir gently into mixture.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes. (I bake mine at 300° or 325° in Bundt pan until done.
Makes it moist.
If using loaf pans, I bake at 350°.)

title: cauliflower cheese bake
directions: Cook cauliflower according to package directions.
Save 1 cup water cauliflower cooked in.
In blender, put cauliflower, 1 cup water from cauliflower, egg, grated sharp cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Blend until mixture is like "whipped" mashed potatoes.
Stir in onion flakes and bacon bits with blender mixture.
Prepare either microwave dish or open casserole dish with grease or Pam.
In conventional oven, cook for 45 minutes at 350°.
Grate a little cheese on top and bake another 5 minutes, or until cheese melts.
In microwave, cook, uncovered, for 7 minutes, then grate a little cheese on top and cook another 2 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Crush crackers.
Season skinned chicken with salt and lemon pepper to taste.
Roll chicken breasts in crackers.
Place in a casserole dish and pour 3 sticks melted butter over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili beans
directions: In large frying pan brown the ground beef and drain excess grease.
In a large crock-pot or large pot, combine all ingredients.
Cook on medium-low heat for 1 1/2 hours, or in crock-pot on low heat overnight.

title: chicken-n-cheese in mushrooms(appetizer or hors d'oeuvres)
directions: Marinate chicken in dressing overnight or longer (2 days). Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Make a small slit in center of each cap to drain off liquid.
Place caps in shallow pan.
Remove a little pulp from stem side and fill with chicken.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and add 1 teaspoon of cheese per mushroom to melt.
Serve hot.
My best friend won $200.00 for this recipe at Frankenmuth, Michigan.

title: hard-cooked egg sandwiches
directions: Combine.
Spread between slices of whole wheat bread or bread of your choice.

title: dirt ball pie
directions: Pour milk into a bowl.
Add pudding mix; beat 1 to 2 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Stir in 1 cup of the cookies and the "rocks."
Spoon into pie crust.
Sprinkle with remaining cookies.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Garnish with gumdrop flowers or gummy worms, if desired.
Great kid's party dessert.

title: beef brisket
directions: Pour desired amount of sweet pickle juice and Liquid Smoke over beef brisket.
Seal in foil.
Bake in low (200°) oven for 4 to 5 hours or vary according to size of brisket.

title: spanish delight
directions: Brown meat, onion and peppers.
Add tomato paste, sauce, water, mushroom soup, salt, pepper and corn.
Cook noodles; drain. Add to beef mixture in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: tapioca pudding(microwave)
directions: Combine milk, 1/4 cup sugar, tapioca and egg yolks in a 2-quart dish; blend well.
Cook on Full power for 6 to 8 minutes, or until mixture begins to boil.
Stir 2 or 3 times during cooking.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually add sugar. Beat in vanilla.
Fold into pudding mixture.
Cool.
Chill, if desired.

title: raspberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease Bundt pan with Crisco and flour. Combine all ingredients and mix 2 minutes.
Bake for 50 minutes.

title: monkey bread cinnamon buns
directions: Cut all biscuits in quarters.
In large plastic bag (with seal), put 3/4 cup sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Put 1/2 of biscuits in bag; seal and shake until coated.
Remove and repeat with other 1/2 of biscuits.
In a small saucepan, heat 1 cup sugar, 1/2 cup margarine and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon until margarine is melted.
Stir off heat until thickened.
Using Bundt pan or ring mold, spray pan with cooking spray and place 1/2 of biscuits in pan.
Cover with margarine mixture.
Place second half of biscuits in pan.
Cover with remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from pan; pull pieces to eat.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Line a 10 x 15-inch cookie pan (use pan with sides) snugly with graham crackers.
Boil brown sugar and butter 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour and spread over crackers and sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and cut.
Makes 1 dozen large cookies or 2 dozen halved.

title: jimmy carter peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add peanut butter and Cool Whip.
Pour into shells and freeze.

title: biscuit topped italian casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
In skillet, brown onion and ground beef; drain.
Stir in water, pepper, tomato sauce and paste.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in veggies and 1 1/2 cups of the cheese.
Spoon mixture into greased baking dish.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits; place near edge over meat mixture, overlap slightly. Gently brush biscuits with oleo.
Sprinkle rest of cheese in center.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Bake 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: grandma's "gravy" bread
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Quickly mix in the cup of water. Press the dough into a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake in a 400° preheated oven for 25 minutes.
Let cool to touch.
Cut into wedges.
It's the perfect bread for "sopping up" meat juices and gravies.

title: pumpkin bread(serves 50)
directions: Mix liquids, then add dry ingredients that have been mixed. Bake in loaf pan, 9 5/8 x 5 1/2 x 2 3/4-inch, for 1 hour at 350°. Makes 21 loaves.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Place the meat and bones into a large soup kettle, cover with water, bring to a boil and simmer for about 5 hours.
After the first two hours season with bay leaf, salt and pepper.
After cooked until tender, cool and cut meat into small pieces and strain the broth.
Add the rest of the ingredients and cook for an additional two hours.

title: roman chow
directions: Brown meat with chopped onions and pepper.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and chopped olives with juice and simmer. Boil egg noodles.
Layer noodles and sauce and cheese.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook eggs and macaroni; cool.
Add remaining ingredients. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix together all ingredients, then drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients together in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Bake in covered casserole for 35 minutes at 350°. Serves 4.

title: swiss chicken and ham roll-ups
directions: In a bowl, mix the chicken, soup (1/3 cup) and onion.
Spoon 1/4 cup of mixture on each ham slice and roll up.
Secure with a wooden toothpick.

title: nutty yams
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Butter a shallow, 2-quart baking dish. Cut yams into quarters.
Put in a large pot of salted water; bring to a boil and cook until tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain, peel and mash.

title: chicken and rice casserole(microwave)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a 10 x 10 x 1 3/4-inch dish. Lay chicken on top of rice mixture.
Cover dish with plastic wrap. Turn back one edge of wrap to allow steam vent.
Cook on High for 20 minutes halfway through cooking time.
Stir rice from corners of dish.
Recover and continue cooking.
Remove plastic wrap and brush chicken with melted butter.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off grease.
Add catsup, taco sauce and seasoning. Simmer for 20 minutes. Wash and cut up lettuce, tomatoes, bell pepper and onion.
Put this in an oval shaped serving dish. Slightly break chips.
Place over lettuce mixture and sprinkle 1 cup grated cheese over this.
Pour sauce over this and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Serves 8.

title: giant chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugars, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat until blended.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla, chocolate chips and pecans.
Divide mixture into thirds.
Spoon each third onto an ungreased cookie sheet, spreading into an 8 1/2-inch circle.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes or until lightly browned.
Gently remove from cookie sheets and let cool on wire racks.
Makes 3 (10-inch) cookies.

title: rowe's original coconut cream pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and cornstarch together with a little cold water.
Heat milk to boiling and add egg mixture and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add coconut (reserve 1/4 cup for top), butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked crust.
Top with meringue (see recipe), sprinkle with remaining coconut and brown in preheated 300 degree oven (for about 20 minutes).

title: deviled crabs
directions: Smooth yolks of hard-boiled eggs in vinegar, mustard and melted butter.
Add seasoning.
Add boiling water, crabmeat, 2 raw egg yolks and bread crumbs.
Chop boiled egg whites fine and add to meat.
Whip raw egg whites and add whipped egg whites.
Fill greased muffin pan and dot each crab cake with 1/4 teaspoon butter.
Use medium heat until browned.
Serve with lemon juice.

title: baked chicken
directions: In
baking
dish, arrange chicken.
Over that put mushroom soup
(undiluted)
and sour cream.
Add onion, pepper and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salisbury steaks
directions: Mix 1/4 cup of soup, beef, crumbs, egg and onion together. Make into 6 patties.
Brown patties; remove fat.
Stir in soup and mushrooms over patties.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover.
Heat for 20 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Add
the
tablespoons
of
sugar and cinnamon to the apples;
stir
and	let
set
for
awhile.	Mix
the remaining ingredients
until smooth.	Fold in apple mixture.	In a Bundt pan or tube pan, layer 1/3 dough first, 1/2 apple mixture, 1/3 dough, 1/2 apple mixture and 1/3 dough.
Bake 1 hour.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Put on top of pecan mixture.
Melt butter and cream cheese in microwave.
Mix in powdered sugar and spoon on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apples with lemon juice. Combine with celery, grapes and mayonnaise. Fold in whipped cream. Chill. Just before serving, add nuts. Serve in a lettuce lined bowl.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Dip beef in boiling water and cover bottom of ungreased baking dish with beef.
Layer with chicken breasts. Add a little salt and pepper to top.
Now put bacon layer on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Take chicken out and drain partially.
Spread chicken with sour cream mixture and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: crystal pound cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt or tube pan.
Thoroughly cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt and add alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Slowly add sugar, still beating, until light colored and fluffy.
Combine butter and hot milk.
Gradually add to egg mixture.
Add sifted dry ingredients and vanilla; mix well.
Bake in a tube pan at 350°, ungreased.
Check after 1/2 hour; will need more, watch carefully.
Take from oven and hang over a glass bottle (upside down) so that it doesn't fall, until very cool.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water with sugar.
Beat eggs, salt and half of flour and mix thoroughly.
Let rise double.
Add melted shortening and mix well.
Add balance of flour to make soft dough.

title: cracker snack
directions: Melt margarine and sugar.
Boil 3 minutes. Pour over crackers. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Sprinkle on chocolate chips and melt. Spread on crackers evenly.
Sprinkle on nuts. Separate crackers and let harden in refrigerator.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: venison casserole
directions: Heat butter or margarine in heavy skillet over medium gas flame (325° to 350° dial setting on controlled burner).
Add salt pork, thinly sliced, and fry until brown.
Remove salt pork from skillet.
Fry breast of venison in hot fat until brown.
Remove venison from skillet.
Blend flour into hot fat.
Add water, stirring until well blended.
Add salt, pepper, garlic, parsley, bay leaf, thyme and onions, thinly sliced.
Add venison and salt pork.
Cover; bring to boil and reduce flame to simmer (200° to 225° dial setting on controlled burner) and continue cooking 1 hour.
Add sliced mushrooms with liquid.
Cover and continue cooking 30 minutes.
Serve with hot steamed white rice.
Serves 8.

title: california skillet
directions: In a large skillet, heat the oil.
Add hamburger and onion. Cook until meat loses its pink color.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese and olives.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in olives.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and cook just until cheese melts.

title: enchiladas
directions: Saute slowly in 1 tablespoon oil:
meat, onions, cumin and salt.
Add tomato paste and chili powder.
Remove from heat and let stand 1 hour.
Soften tortillas and in each place 3 tablespoons meat mixture, 1 tablespoon green onions and 2 tablespoons of cheese.
Place in baking dish and top with chili beans and remaining cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: cucumber and onion salad
directions: Arrange cucumbers and onions in an 8-inch square dish. Combine remaining ingredients in a jar. Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Pour dressing over cucumbers and onions, stirring gently. Cover and chill at least 3 hours.
Yields 8 servings.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 3 teaspoons sugar together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch
pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip together and spread on cooled pretzel mixture.
Mix jello, boiling water and strawberries. Place in refrigerator until it begins to gel.
Pour over pan mixture.
Refrigerate until set.

title: quick barbecued chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce overall.
Bake 1 hour, basting once in awhile until chicken is cooked through at 350°.

title: arroz con pollo
directions: Brown one cut-up frying chicken or chicken pieces in 4 tablespoons butter; set aside.
Brown 1 package chicken Rice-A-Roni in 2 tablespoons butter.
Remove to 3-quart casserole. Stir in 2 cups boiling water, contents of chicken flavor packet, stewed tomatoes and salt.
Arrange browned chicken on top.
Cover and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Uncover the last 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
(Can be cooked in an electric skillet.)

title: salsa dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: cheese stuffed potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and dry.
Rub lightly with salad oil.
Bake at 450° for 45 to 60 minutes (or microwave according to directions). When done, cut in halves and scoop out insides.
Mash potatoes. Add evaporated milk and whip until light and fluffy.
Add remaining seasonings.
Fold in cheese and spread top with butter. Brown about 10 minutes (or sprinkle with paprika and microwave just until cheese melts).

title: butterscotch morsel candy
directions: Mix in double boiler.
Stir over heat until melted.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat and add 1 can Borden condensed milk.
Mix well and pour in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cooled.

title: orange fruit cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs (one at a time) and grated orange rind. Then add nuts, flour and salt, sifted together, alternately with sugar and sour milk, add flour last, then dates. Bake for 1 hour at 350° or 2 hours at 300°.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients and serve with all kinds of vegetables.

title: banana bread
directions: Smash bananas.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Combine meat, tomato juice, onion, seasonings and 6 cups water in soup kettle.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Trim meat and cut in cubes.
Strain broth and skim off excess fat.
Return meat and add vegetables.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: martha washingtons
directions: Combine confectioners sugar, milk, coconut, walnuts and butter. Mix well.
Roll into balls.
Dip into melted chocolate as needed. Place on waxed paper to set chocolate.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Make vanilla pudding according to directions on box.
Add Eagle Brand milk.
Pour over vanilla wafers and bananas in large bowl.
Top with Cool Whip.
Let chill one hour.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Mix flour, spices and soda; add alternately with buttermilk.
Add nuts and cooked prunes.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: carrot-pineapple bread
directions: Combine all the ingredients. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into two greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: johnny cake
directions: Mix sugar and shortening well; add eggs.
Sift four and cornmeal; add soda to buttermilk.
Alternate buttermilk and flour and cornmeal.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix dry pudding with crushed pineapple with juice, whipped topping, marshmallows and apples.
Chill.
Add peanuts just before serving.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs. Heat applesauce and while still warm, add soda, then add butter, sugar and egg mixture. Add other ingredients except raisins and nuts. Mix well. Add raisins and nuts last. Raisins and nuts may be coated in some of previous flour. Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake with low heat for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt shortening.
Beat egg with sugar.
Add melted shortening, sour milk and rolled oats.
Blend well.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder together.
Add spices, then add to first mixture. Mix until well blended.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix juices and sweeten to taste.
Chill.
Pour chilled ingredients over ice block in a punch bowl.
Just before serving, add ginger beer.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: double crispy chicken
directions: Mix egg and milk.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in the egg batter, then in the crushed corn flakes.
Place a single layer, skin side up in a greased or foil lined pan.
Drip melted butter on top of chicken and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not cover the pan or turn chicken while baking.

title: twin sauerbraten loaves
directions: Add crumbs to 1 cup water and let stand a few minutes.
Add meat and next 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into 2 loaves and brown on both sides in the butter in skillet.
Combine 1 cup water and remaining ingredients except flour and add to meat loaves. Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer, basting several times with liquid in skillet and turning once, about 1 hour.
Remove loaves, skim fat from liquid and thicken with flour mixed with a little water.
Simmer a few minutes, adding a "little" more water if necessary.
Strain and pour over sliced meat.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peach delicious
directions: Mix together.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: egg rolls
directions: Boil chicken for 1 hour; debone and break into small pieces. Chop the rest of the ingredients into small pieces.
Cook pork and garlic, then add onion, then celery, then bell pepper, then cabbage, then bean sprouts, then chicken.
Remove from heat; drain and cool.
Start wrapping, putting 1 spoonful in each wrapper. Seal with a little egg on the edge of wrapper.
Deep fry in hot oil.
Uncooked egg rolls may be frozen until ready to eat.

title: party potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute green peppers, green onions and pimento in margarine in skillet for 1 minute.
Stir in flour, parsley flakes, salt, pepper and paprika.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add 1 cup cheese; mix well.
Spoon potatoes into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour sauce over potatoes, stirring to coat.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Yields 12 servings.

title: cream cheese and beef dip
directions: You can use a blender to mix everything into cream cheese. Mix well. Refrigerate. You can use as a dip or roll into balls.

title: frozen grasshopper pie
directions: Or use 1 prepared chocolate crust.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and drain broccoli.
Mix with green onions, bacon bits and croutons.
Put salad dressing on before meal.

title: soft whole wheat pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw bread in refrigerator overnight. From each loaf, shape 12 (1 1/2-inch) balls.
Roll each ball into a rope approximately 14 inches long.
Shape into pretzels by forming a knot and loop ends through.
Arrange pretzels 1-inch apart on well-greased baking sheet.
Let stand for 20 minutes. Brush combined egg white and water mix on pretzels, then sprinkle with salt.
Place a shallow pan containing 1-inch boiling water on lower rack in oven.
Bake until brown, 20 minutes, approximately above water.

title: dilled chicken
directions: Take mustard, dill weed, pineapple juice and brown sugar. Mix, then set aside.
Take each chick breast and wrap with strip of bacon.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spoon the sauce over chicken and bake in oven at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil until fluffy.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in greased loaf pans (2) at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.
Ice with cream cheese icing.

title: apricot skillet pork chops
directions: Cook chops in butter in electric skillet (350°).
Remove from skillet and keep warm.
Mix cornstarch and sugar; add to skillet along with peels, seasonings and juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce boils (1/2 minute).
Add raisins.
Reduce heat to 225°.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Place chops in skillet and heat.
Add apricots and onion just before serving and heat.
Spoon sauce over chops and serve with apricots on chops.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables until almost done.
Put in pan or crock-pot with soups, ham and milk.
Flavor with salt and pepper.
Cook. Before serving, add cheese to melt.

title: viennese sandwich cookies
directions: In covered blender or food processor, blend half of the almonds at one time until finely ground.
Measure flour, butter, sugar and salt into large bowl.
Add ground almonds.
With hands, knead ingredients until well blended (dough will be very dry). Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll out half of dough at a time between two sheets of wax paper.
With a 1/2-inch round cutter, cut out cookies, place 1/2 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove with spatula to wire racks; cool.
Evenly spread a bit of apricot preserves on half the cookies.
Top with remaining cookies.
Prepare Chocolate Glaze. Dip filled cookies edgewise into chocolate mixture to cover 1/2 cookie.
Place on waxed paper to dry.
Store in refrigerator. Makes 3 1/2 to 4 dozen.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cut candy into small pieces into the flour. Add sugar and mix well.
Beat eggs into mixture. Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well. May need to use hands.
Grease and flour 2 (8 x 10-inch) pans and line with brown paper. Fill with mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.
Remove paper.
Cut into squares. Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: peachy crumble
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, oatmeal, butter and cinnamon; mix until crumbly.
Line bottom and sides of a 9-inch square baking dish with half of mixture; press firmly.
Add peaches.
Boil together sugar, cornstarch and water until clear.
Add vanilla. Pour over peaches and cover with remaining half of crumb mixture. Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: mexican dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature until spreadable. Spread evenly into a glass 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with chili and beans; spread evenly.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350° until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Serve with chips.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Melt margarine in large shallow baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients and spoon onto melted margarine.
Batter will be stiff.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: instant french toast
directions: Put bread into toaster for 2 minutes, then spread with butter and add syrup to taste.
Then, you have French toast.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix spices and baking powder with sugar.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Mix butter with potatoes.
Mix all of these ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 45 minutes.
It will make you shut your mouth in a flash.

title: corn casserole(club member: laine shoemake)
directions: Mix all ingredients. Put into a slightly greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: baked mock chow mein
directions: Add the onions, celery and soups to the ground beef. Rinse cans with the warm water. Add the rice and soy sauce. Pour into a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, then sprinkle top with chow mein noodles and bake another 15 minutes longer.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Boil juice; stir in jello to dissolve.
Add strawberries. Barely thicken; add drained crushed pineapple.
Set this mixture aside to use as third layer.

title: ziti bake
directions: Prepare ziti according to the label; drain and set aside. Cook ground beef until well browned.
In a large bowl, combine drained ground beef, Ricotta, Parmesan, parsley, egg, salt, pepper and half the spaghetti sauce.
Mix well.
Add ziti and toss gently to coat well.
In a large lasagna pan or 13 x 9-inch pan, spoon the mixture evenly.
Pour the remaining sauce over the ziti.
Then sprinkle the Mozzarella over the whole thing.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hot buttered rum mix
directions: In a large bowl, cream the butter and the sugars together until smooth. Add the softened ice cream and mix until a creamy consistency is obtained. Transfer this to a freezer container with a tight-fitting lid. Place in the freezer for up to 1 month.

title: dipper's funnels
directions: Pour oil into a large skillet to depth of 1-inch.
Heat over medium heat to 360°.
Mix egg and milk into small bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Holding finger under funnel opening, pour 1/4 cup batter into funnel.
Starting in center of skillet, allow batter to run through funnel into oil and circle around to form spiral shape.
Add milk as needed to thin batter.
Fry for 1 minute on each side.
Drain on paper towels. Sprinkle lightly with powdered sugar or serve with syrup.
Makes 6 cakes.

title: chocolate chunk-peanut butter ice cream
directions: Beat eggs at high speed of an electric mixer.
Add sugar and peanut butter; beat well.
Stir in candy bars and evaporated milk, mixing until combined.
Stir in milk.
Pour mixture into freezer can of a 5-quart hand-turned or electric freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Let ice cream ripen at least 1 hour.
Yields about 1 gallon.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Sift sugar, flour and cocoa.
Beat egg yolks in milk.
Mix together and cook until thick.
Stir vanilla and margarine in. Pour in a cool baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown 15 to 20 minutes.

title: company's a coming
directions: Beat egg
whites until frothy.	Add cream of tartar and sugar; beat until stiff.	Crumble saltines, pecans and vanilla.
Mix gently
with
egg
whites.	Spread	in
buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and
cook
minutes at 350°.
Cool completely. Mix
preserves and Cool Whip; spread over meringue.
Sprinkle with
coconut. Refrigerate
hours.
Any
preserves may be used.
Pineapple and apricot are very good.	Serves 24.

title: crisp cucumber pickles
directions: Place all ingredients, except cukes, in a 1/2 gallon container with cover.
Cover and shake until sugar dissolves.
Pack cukes in a jar.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.
Ready to eat when they are chilled.

title: blueberry angel food cake rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 2 (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch) jelly roll pans with aluminum foil.
Prepare cake following package directions.
Divide batter into lined pans; spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until set.
Invert cake at once onto towels dusted with confectioners sugar.
Remove foil carefully.
Roll up each cake with towel jelly roll fashion.
Cool completely.
Unroll cake.
Spread 1 cup of blueberry pie filling on each cake.
Re-roll and place, seam side down, on serving plate.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; save 1 1/2 cups broth.
Remove chicken from bones (or use boneless breast).
Melt margarine.
Pour dressing mix in butter.
In
casserole dish, place 1 layer of chicken and 1 layer dressing mix.
Start with dressing mix.
Put chicken on last.
Pour broth and cream soup over casserole.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: steak and pork chop marinade
directions: Recipe makes enough for 6 thick steaks or chops. Meat is better if marinated overnight and 2 hours at room temperature prior to grilling.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, folding in whipped topping last.

title: pork chops spanish style
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
Brown meat in hot shortening.
Drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 1 1/2-quart greased baking dish, combine tomatoes with liquid, rice, butter and 1 teaspoon salt.
Arrange meat over rice.
Bake for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Serves 4.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix the last 2 ingredients together and set aside. Mix the first 7 ingredients. Chill dough. Roll dough into balls (teaspoon size). Roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix well.
Divide into 8 to 10 balls.
Roll in chopped pecans. Refrigerate.

title: cream dry beef chicken
directions: You can either make this recipe in a crock-pot or in the oven. If in a crock-pot, let cook 8 hours on low setting.
In oven, bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except 1 cup cheese for topping. Dot with butter.
Place in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle remaining cup of cheese on top. Top with some Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: pie crust(can also be used for homemade pizza crust.)
directions: Mix all ingredients and pat into pan.
Bake depending on what you are using it for.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Steam broccoli and onion with chicken broth until tender. Drain, keeping broth.
Chop broccoli in food processor.
Melt butter and add flour to make roux.
Add broth, salt and pepper. Cook until thick and add half and half and cheese.
Cook on low heat until cheese is melted, then add broccoli.

title: caramel oatmeal chewies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: shrimp louis dip
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain pineapple and use juice to dissolve the pudding.
Mix pineapple, Cool Whip, marshmallows and pecans together.
Add mixture to pudding and stir until well blended.
Chill.

title: sour cream chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, cool and pull off bone into bite sized pieces. Mix sour cream, soup, broth and seasoning together with chicken. (You may need to add more broth to get the right consistency. Mixture doesn't need to be too thick, but not runny.)

title: rice balls
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Transfer hot rice into large aluminum pan.
Stir in butter until melted.
Add cheese and egg yolks.
Mix well.
Cover.
Chill overnight.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.

title: evelyn's turkey marinade
directions: Marinate turkey breast cutlets in mixture for 24 hours. Grill.

title: swiss french bread
directions: Melt margarine, add green onion, lemon juice, poppy seeds, mustard, and seasoned salt.
Mix until well blended.
Spread on both halves of the French bread.
Top
margarine mixture with 1/2 pound grated cheese on each loaf half.
Place both halves side by side on aluminum foil.
Do not cover.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Can be served as bread at a meal or cut into smaller pieces and served as appetizers.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Set aside.
Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugars.
Add to shortening mixture, milk, egg and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Take 1 teaspoon at a time and shape into ball.
Roll in sugar.
Bake for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and put a Hershey's Kiss in center of each cookie.
Put back in oven for 2 to 5 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour until particles are like fine crumbs.
Add milk and stir with a fork only until dough leaves the side of the bowl.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, powdered sugar and salt.
Add oleo, egg and vanilla. Pat into pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Dissolve soda in boiling water; add along with orange juice.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Add mashed bananas.
Mix and add nuts, if desired.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 1 large or 2 small loaves.

title: country club goulash
directions: Cook livers by themselves until tender.
Let juice boil down to about 2 cups of juice.
Pressure cook gizzards about 1 hour on low.
Add 2 tablespoons corn oil; stir in onions and peppers and put lid on for a while and stir down.
Mix together cooked livers and gizzards; pour in onions and peppers.
Use the oil from onions, add 1/2 cup flour and brown like gravy (thick).
Take juice from livers and gizzards; pour all together.
Bring to boil. Serve over rice.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Cream butter.
Add oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to butter mixture.
Blend well.
Add chocolate chips and zucchini (1/2 cup nuts may be added, if desired).
Stir to combine.
Pour into prepared pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: texas beef skillet(serves 6)
directions: In skillet, cook ground beef and onion until brown.
Sprinkle meat mixture with chili powder, salt and garlic salt.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, undrained beans, uncooked rice, water and green peppers.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally for 20 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Cover and heat until cheese melts, about 3 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with crushed corn chips if desired.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: In a large bowl, beat together the eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick and foamy.
Stir in the zucchini and the crushed pineapple.
Combine the flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg, and add to the zucchini mixture.
Stir in the chopped nuts.
Pour into 2 loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all together.
Will be lumpy.
Fry on griddle or waffle iron.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix the meat with the soups.
Pour into a casserole dish and top with Tater Tots.
Bake in a 350° oven until it bubbles.

title: dr. birdsong cake
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and sugar.
Dice bananas and add to dry ingredients, along with oil, vanilla, eggs and crushed pineapple with juice.
Mixture is stirred but not beaten.
Pour into a greased 9-inch tube pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
(Check at 1 hour to see if it is done.)
When done, let cool before removing from pan.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: *spinach with rice
directions: Saute the onion in heated oil until golden. Add the remaining ingredients and cook over low heat until done, about 30 minutes.

title: marinated pork tenderloin
directions: Mix all ingredients in a plastic bag and marinate pork tenderloins in the refrigerator for 2 to 3 days.
Drain meat but reserve marinade.
Grill 20 minutes, turning once.

title: unfried french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a cookie sheet with Pam.
Wash potatoes well.
Cut potatoes into French fry size pieces, leaving on the skin.
In a large bowl, combine egg whites and seasonings. Add potatoes to mixture, making sure each piece is covered.
Put potatoes on the sprayed cookie sheet.
Cook until brown, turning so they brown evenly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken (do not salt).
Remove from bone, cut up and set aside.
Save broth.
Mix stuffing and melted butter.

title: creamy corn and roasted pepper chowder
directions: In a pot over high heat combine potatoes and enough water to cover.
Boil, reduce heat and simmer until tender (about 30 minutes).
Drain, cool and cut into small pieces or chunks.
In large pot over high heat combine broth, 4 cups corn, onion, leek and salt.
Boil, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes. In a food processor or blender, process soup until smooth.
Return to pot. Add remaining 2 cups corn, bring to boil.
Remove from heat and stir in roasted red peppers and potatoes.
Prep time:
30 minutes, cook time: 50 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut butter popcorn
directions: Pop popcorn in shortening.
Place in bowl.
Combine sugar and syrup in saucepan.
Over low heat, bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla. Pour over popcorn; mix well.
Pour onto cookie sheet; cool.

title: cool whip dessert
directions: Dip cookies in milk.
Layer Cool Whip and cookies. Refrigerate overnight.

title: hot doggies in sauce
directions: Mix all together.
Simmer over low heat for 45 minutes.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions.
Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed and salt.
Pour over cucumbers and onions in a freezer container. The mixture must cover the cucumbers.
Store in refrigerator 4 days and then freeze.

title: chicken pie
directions: Melt
stick of margarine in a 9 x 14-inch square pan. Cook chicken; debone it and cut into pieces. Heat chicken broth and chicken
soup
until
hot.	Pour over chicken and then put into buttered
pan.
In	bowl
mix
flour,
salt, milk, baking powder and
pepper
together.
Pour batter over top of chicken mixture and
spread
it
to
cover the top. This will make the crust. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: french toast
directions: Dip slices of bread into egg batter, one slice at a time. Place egg covered bread into skillet preheated with margarine. Fry both sides until lightly brown.
Serve with syrup.

title: french potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes thinly (use food processor if available).
Lightly grease casserole dish.
Layer with potato slices.
Sprinkle each layer with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Press garlic over mixture.
Add cream and milk.
Bake at 400° for about 40 minutes or until potatoes are soft, creamy and golden brown.

title: frozen italian fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, combine mashed bananas and pineapple and let stand 5 minutes. Add whipped topping, sour cream, sugar, fruit cocktail, cherries (and pecans, if desired).
Combine well and freeze in 9 x 11-inch dish or individual serving dishes. Serves 18 to 20.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours, until potatoes are done.
Top casserole with Cheddar cheese.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate-covered raisin cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Cream butter with brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Mix together dry ingredients with butter mixture.
Mix in chocolate-covered raisins.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix everything together but the crackers. Put the crackers on top. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, flour, vanilla and pecans.
Roll into long roll.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill overnight or a few hours or days.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Put the ice cream in a large mixing bowl.
Allow to melt slightly, enough to where it is soft enough to mix. Add whipped cream and crushed Oreos and mix until the cookies are mixed evenly.
Pour into freezer-proof cake pan.
Lay whole cookies on top. Cover and place in freezer.
Serve after ice cream solidifies.

title: rhode island red
directions: Boil onions in water to cover; drain.
Chop tomatoes fine. Cut cheese in small dice.
When onions are done, add tomatoes and cheese to saucepan.
Stir constantly to blend.
Serve over pieces of broken hard bread.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and cocoa.
In saucepan, mix margarine and water and bring to a rapid boil.
Add to flour, sugar and cocoa.
Stir until well blended.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Pour into large cookie sheet pan.
Bake 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: change of pace swiss steak
directions: Brown steak in electric skillet or on stove. Remove excess grease. Add chopped celery and onions. Pour on top of steak; add tomato sauce. Cover and let simmer until vegetables are cooked as you desire. If needed, add some water so sauce is plentiful. May be served over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: cranberry-mallows pie
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in the boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened. Fold in the cranberry sauce and pineapple. Pour into chilled crust.
Chill until firm.
Melt the marshmallows with the milk in double boiler. Stir until smooth.
Add the vanilla and food coloring.
Chill until thickened.
Mix until well blended.
Fold in the whipped cream.
Spread over pie filling. Chill until firm.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and onions.
Brown hamburger with taco seasoning mix.
Cool and add to salad.
Chill.
Add dressing (Thousand Island, taco or mayonnaise and ketchup).
Add taco chips just before serving.
Can add salsa over salad for spiciness.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Cook almonds and sugar (3 tablespoons) over low heat.
Stir while cooking until caramelized.
Spread on aluminum foil sprayed with Pam.
Allow to cool, then break into small pieces.
Mix salt, pepper, oil, parsley, sugar and vinegar in bowl or salad dressing container (you may want to double the amount of dressing if you like a lot).
Chill until ready.

title: pickled carrots
directions: Mix undiluted soup, oil, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire, salt and pepper.
Do not cook.
Pour over carrots, onion and green pepper.
Cover in bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Will keep at least a week in refrigerator.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Prepare one day ahead of time.
Cube bread into 1 1/2-inch square pieces and place in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Fry and drain meat.
Crumble it evenly over bread layer.
Sprinkle grated cheese over meat layer.
Combine eggs, salt, milk, dry mustard and drizzle evenly over bread, meat and cheese.
Cover with foil and allow it to sit overnight in the refrigerator.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
(Great for weekend guests or holiday brunch.)

title: green beans almondine
directions: Cook beans in small amount of water until tender.
Drain. Melt butter and saute almonds until light brown. Remove almonds and saute the mushrooms in the butter.
Mix together and season to taste.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place
yeast
in
cups
warm water.
Melt margarine, cream with
sugar
in
a large bowl.
Then add beaten egg; add dissolved yeast
to creamed mixture.
Then add flour and stir until mixed. Place in airtight bowl and keep in refrigerator. Batter
will
be very
thin.
To
bake, drop by spoonful into well-greased
2 1/2-inch muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes
or until browned.
This dough keeps for 7 days in refrigerator. Batter
does not need to rise.
May be baked as soon as made up.

title: cocoa syrup
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa in a pan.
Add sufficient water to make paste, then add remainder of water.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour at once into jar.
Makes 2 cups.

title: mexican goulash
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion.
Add soup, Velveeta, tortillas and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: dream cake(can be prepared the day before.)
directions: Base:
Mix together and spread in a 9 x 15-inch dish the oleo and chopped nuts. Press down and bake at 325° for 25 minutes and cool.

title: chocolate chunk brownies
directions: Toast the nuts by spreading in a single layer in a shallow pan. Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Melt the butter; add the sugar, eggs, cocoa and vanilla.
Combine the flour and baking powder and stir into the chocolate mixture.
Coarsely chop the chocolate squares, keeping in large chunks.
Stir the nuts and chocolate into the batter.
Spread batter into an 8 x 8-inch baking pan that is lightly greased.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick comes out barely moist.
Cool in pan on a rack.
Cut into squares.

title: friendship bread
directions: Mix well and pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Let cool 10 minutes before removing from pans. Freezes well.

title: luau spareribs
directions: Place ribs in a shallow baking dish, meaty side up.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons water.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes; drain off fat.
In a saucepan, combine orange juice, water, brown sugar, vinegar, honey, mustard, salt and pepper.
Heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over ribs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, basting every 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with green onions and garnish with watercress (optional) and orange slices.

title: glazed chicken wings
directions: Combine only 2 tablespoons soy sauce, 1 tablespoon lemon juice from concentrate and ginger.
Pour over chicken, stirring to coat. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining 2 tablespoons soy sauce, 1 tablespoon lemon juice from concentrate, honey and 1 tablespoon water.

title: caramel rolls(easy)
directions: Melt together first 4 ingredients in microwave. Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan. Place frozen rolls in pan. Cover and raise overnight. Bake at 350° for
25 to 30 minutes until dark brown. Flip onto cookie sheet and eat.

title: kraut slaw
directions: Put kraut juice and sugar in a pan. Heat until sugar is dissolved. Cool. Pour over all other ingredients; mix well. Let set overnight for best flavor. Serves about 6.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Melt oil and butter in large cookie sheet with sides to prevent mixture from running out.
Spread pecans over tray, stirring to coat with mixture.
Bake at 250° for one hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with salt, stirring to distribute salt evenly.

title: sausage and cheese surprise
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Add all remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Turn off burner; add chunks of cheese.
Cover and let cool with burner off.
After cheese has melted, mix thoroughly.
Spread each slice of bread and place them, in single layer, on cookie sheets.
Place in freezer until frozen.
Remove and place bread in plastic bags; return to freezer.
When ready to eat, place on cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal rolls
directions: Mix oatmeal and boiling water and allow to cool to lukewarm. Mix sugar, yeast and warm water and let stand 5 minutes.
Mix these ingredients with all other ingredients and mix well.
Knead on a floured board until elastic.
Put in greased bowl and let rise. Shape into rolls and let rise again.
Bake at 375° about 25 minutes.

title: new orleans' pralines
directions: Caramelize 1/2 cup of sugar in a saucepan.
In the meantime, have the 2
cups of sugar and Pet milk in another large saucepan and put on fire and let boil real good.
Pour caramelized sugar into it and stir good.
Let boil up until it forms a soft ball. Take off fire and add butter.
Beat until creamy and drop by tablespoonfuls to make a large New Orleans size patty.
(This recipe is creamy, not grainy.)

title: party pizza
directions: Spread Philadelphia cream cheese on large dinner plate. Spread cocktail sauce on cheese.
Sprinkle ingredients as listed, using amount to cover plate.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Serve with party crackers.

title: jello icebox pie
directions: Mix together
Jell-O
and
boiling water and cool.
Whip Pet milk.
Add sugar
and whip again.
Add juice of 1 lemon and whip again.
Fold
in Jell-O mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.
I prefer to make cookie crust and use.

title: plum nutty cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sausage hot dish(for 6 to 8 people)
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Put cubed bread in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish, buttered.
Top with cheese.
Put sausage on top of this.
Beat eggs with 2 1/4 cups milk and the mustard and pour over sausage mixture.
Refrigerate this overnight.
Next day take soup, dilute with 1/4 cup milk and pour over all.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300° and serve hot.
(This is great for a brunch.
Also, can be made using cooked chicken pieces or cut up ham, replacing the sausage.)

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients above; mix well. Spoon into a 2 qt. casserole dish. Cover with topping.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Mix soup, enchilada sauce and undrained beans.
Add drained meat.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix 1 can of mixed vegetables and 1 can cream of chicken; dried onion can be mixed in (dried onion is optional).
Put cheese on top of the casserole.
Crush Ritz crackers and use that as a topping.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rice shrimp salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Prepare 24 hours prior to serving. Add additional dressing if necessary before serving.

title: veg-all goulash
directions: Brown meat in large, heavy pan.
Add chopped onion and let cook until onion wilts.
Cook macaroni according to directions on package, drain and add to meat.
Add all other ingredients.
Cover and cook very slowly for 30 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Measure all ingredients and put them in blender.
Mix well, about 5 minutes.
Refrigerate.

title: pasta pot with meat and veggies
directions: Dice chop the celery and set aside.
Extra celery goes good in the garden salad.

title: macaroon cookies
directions: Cut crust from bread.
Cut into 3-inch strips.
Dip in Eagle Bread milk.
Roll in coconut.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add salt and sugar.
Blend in flour; knead on floured surface.
Roll strips.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Brush with egg; sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, or until brown.
Serve warm.

title: creole cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with hand mixer and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat, garlic, salt, pepper and oregano.
Add tomato paste, water and tomatoes; simmer 20 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Mix cottage cheese and Swiss cheese.
Layer meat, cheese and noodles, beginning and ending with meat sauce.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Place 1/2 of croutons on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, beat together eggs and milk; stir in onion, celery and salad dressing.
Combine butter, hot water and remaining croutons.
Fold into egg mixture, stirring well.
In pan, alternate layers of chicken and crouton mixture, ending with crouton mixture.
Let refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, pour soup over the top and sprinkle with your favorite cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 12 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add eggs, then dry ingredients.
Add bananas, stir in nuts.

title: potato and olive salad
directions: Cook potatoes with skins in boiling water in small pan until tender.
Drain; peel if desired, and dice into bite size pieces. Place in serving bowl along with capers and olives.

title: woodstove chicken casserole
directions: Steam chicken until it is tender.
Remove bones and skin.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Mix water and mushroom soup in a bowl until smooth.
